WEBVTT

1
00:01:48.600 --> 00:01:51.719
It isn't gonna be a problem.
all right? OK?

2
00:01:51.720 --> 00:01:54.840
Listen. don't talk to anyone.
all right?

3
00:02:05.080 --> 00:02:08.399
He used to know a guy
that runs a garage in Munich.

4
00:02:08.400 --> 00:02:10.399
Said if you needed a vehicle
under the radar.

5
00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:13.440
false plates or a stolen car.
then he was your man.

6
00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:19.800
I'm thinking I should go.
To Munich?

7
00:02:20.760 --> 00:02:22.159
You can't go to Munich.

8
00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:25.239
Albazi's prosecution needs
solid evidence.

9
00:02:25.240 --> 00:02:27.639
And Marcel Kullen
can't reopen the investigation

10
00:02:27.640 --> 00:02:30.399
into Sandy's suicide
without a concrete lead.

11
00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.519
Look. we get intel on the car
that drove into Sandy in Munich.

12
00:02:33.520 --> 00:02:36.360
then we can verify if
it really was a drink-drive offence.

13
00:02:37.480 --> 00:02:40.079
What if it was Albazi. hm?

14
00:02:40.080 --> 00:02:42.359
Or one of his men...

15
00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:43.999
who was behind the wheel that day?

16
00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:45.400
I... I don't know. Glenn.

17
00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:49.200
It's too risky.

18
00:02:51.880 --> 00:02:53.439
Man.

19
00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:54.920
You said it yourself.

20
00:02:56.200 --> 00:03:00.000
Bruno isn't safe
until we put Albazi away for good.

21
00:03:01.960 --> 00:03:03.799
Mate...

22
00:03:03.800 --> 00:03:07.840
how long do you want this secret
to be hanging over your family for?

23
00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:11.199
If anyone should go.
it should be me.

24
00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:14.120
No. No. no. no.
No. you're too close to it.

25
00:03:15.520 --> 00:03:17.240
You'd just attract attention.

26
00:03:24.680 --> 00:03:26.640
OK. Yeah. all right.

27
00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:29.279
Bella?

28
00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:31.839
'Roy. we've got a body
washed up at the Sea Lock.'

29
00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:33.600
OK. We're on our way.
ENGINE STARTS

30
00:03:51.640 --> 00:03:54.199
The victim's been ID'd
from her university lanyard

31
00:03:54.200 --> 00:03:55.519
as Charlie Downing.

32
00:03:55.520 --> 00:03:57.879
A psychology student at Sussex Met.

33
00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:59.400
She's just turned 20.

34
00:04:00.960 --> 00:04:02.240
Christ. Poor kid.

35
00:04:04.160 --> 00:04:05.840
Have we notified next of kin?

36
00:04:07.120 --> 00:04:09.599
Parents deceased. No siblings.

37
00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:11.240
Well. someone's missing her.

38
00:04:17.960 --> 00:04:22.079
And what if they've been
through a rehabilitation programme?

39
00:04:22.080 --> 00:04:23.959
Would that convince you?
No.

40
00:04:23.960 --> 00:04:27.879
Some prisoners have only served
40% of their sentence.

41
00:04:27.880 --> 00:04:29.479
That's less than half.

42
00:04:29.480 --> 00:04:31.559
Effectively.
it's a get-out-of-jail-free card.

43
00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:33.000
Excellent. Maddie.

44
00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:37.400
Bronwyn... what do you think?

45
00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:43.000
Well. 200 million's been put
into support services...

46
00:04:44.200 --> 00:04:47.719
...to make sure that they
don't go back to crime. Yeah.

47
00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:50.000
Mr Welling... has it worked?

48
00:04:51.120 --> 00:04:52.679
No. It hasn't.

49
00:04:52.680 --> 00:04:55.359
Rehabilitation's cut short
when a prisoner's released.

50
00:04:55.360 --> 00:04:57.759
so what's the point?
It's a waste of tax payers' money.

51
00:04:57.760 --> 00:05:00.359
OK. But if we're bringing offenders
back into the community.

52
00:05:00.360 --> 00:05:02.879
doesn't that show that we care?

53
00:05:02.880 --> 00:05:05.960
What about victims?
Who cares about them?

54
00:05:08.040 --> 00:05:10.119
Well. isn't there
an argument to be made

55
00:05:10.120 --> 00:05:12.879
that preventing repeat crimes
through rehabilitations is...

56
00:05:14.120 --> 00:05:17.000
...is it economically more viable
in the long run?

57
00:05:19.240 --> 00:05:21.840
Guys. Phones. please.

58
00:05:27.800 --> 00:05:29.679
Time of death is difficult
to pinpoint.

59
00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:33.839
but I would estimate
between 7:30 and 8:30pm last night.

60
00:05:33.840 --> 00:05:37.439
And these compression points here
indicate strangulation.

61
00:05:37.440 --> 00:05:39.679
Dead before she entered the water?

62
00:05:39.680 --> 00:05:43.600
The postmortem will confirm.
but most likely. yes.

63
00:05:45.160 --> 00:05:47.879
What about the scratch?
A sign of a struggle. maybe?

64
00:05:47.880 --> 00:05:51.519
Difficult to tell. given the water
submersion and potential predation.

65
00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:54.199
She may have been carried down
the river before entering the lock.

66
00:05:54.200 --> 00:05:55.760
which could've caused the abrasion.

67
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:08.480
Davey... where were you last night?

68
00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.720
We were supposed to speak. so why
weren't you answering your phone?

69
00:06:18.360 --> 00:06:21.519
You do realise that
if you don't report to me every day.

70
00:06:21.520 --> 00:06:23.120
you're at risk of recall to prison.

71
00:06:25.640 --> 00:06:27.120
I was with my girlfriend.

72
00:06:28.920 --> 00:06:30.840
Ex-girlfriend.

73
00:06:32.520 --> 00:06:33.760
I see.

74
00:06:36.600 --> 00:06:38.160
Well. I am sorry to hear that.

75
00:06:40.200 --> 00:06:41.639
Did something happen between you?

76
00:06:41.640 --> 00:06:43.999
Is... Is that
why you couldn't pick up?

77
00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:46.680
Davey? She just doesn't wanna see me
any more.

78
00:06:50.080 --> 00:06:51.560
Who would blame her?

79
00:06:53.440 --> 00:06:55.520
Have you spoken to the doctor?

80
00:06:59.040 --> 00:07:01.280
Cos. you know.
if you're feeling low. she can help.

81
00:07:02.440 --> 00:07:06.320
They could up your meds maybe.
or find you someone to talk to.

82
00:07:08.960 --> 00:07:10.320
I know it's not easy.

83
00:07:12.040 --> 00:07:14.279
And it's not gonna be easy
for a long time.

84
00:07:14.280 --> 00:07:15.800
but I promise you...

85
00:07:17.600 --> 00:07:19.440
...you can have a good life.

86
00:07:21.320 --> 00:07:22.480
You can.

87
00:07:26.160 --> 00:07:27.519
If she surfaced here.

88
00:07:27.520 --> 00:07:30.159
she could've been dumped anywhere
along the river.

89
00:07:30.160 --> 00:07:32.840
I'm organising a search.
OK.

90
00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:35.400
Who are they?

91
00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:38.159
University students.

92
00:07:38.160 --> 00:07:40.599
It's already all over social media.

93
00:07:40.600 --> 00:07:41.960
We need to head down to campus.

94
00:07:43.160 --> 00:07:45.399
Find out about Charlie's movements
last night.

95
00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:46.920
Cheers.

96
00:08:07.880 --> 00:08:09.920
"Student loses her life." She...

97
00:08:11.240 --> 00:08:13.680
She didn't lose her life.
She was murdered.

98
00:08:15.080 --> 00:08:18.360
I've been saying something like this
was going to happen for months.

99
00:08:22.800 --> 00:08:26.560
Repost our appeal for information.
We need to get this trending.

100
00:08:32.160 --> 00:08:33.919
"Action Vigilant"?
Yeah.

101
00:08:33.920 --> 00:08:36.879
It's their whistle-blowing
social media platform.

102
00:08:36.880 --> 00:08:38.919
Appealing for tip offs.
exposing cover ups.

103
00:08:38.920 --> 00:08:40.120
you know. that sort of thing.

104
00:08:43.160 --> 00:08:45.960
70.000 followers. and it's growing.

105
00:08:50.200 --> 00:08:52.040
I've been looking
for you everywhere.

106
00:08:54.200 --> 00:08:55.560
Are you OK?

107
00:08:58.480 --> 00:08:59.920
Did you hear what happened?

108
00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.280
Are you gonna tell someone?

109
00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:08.440
I-I can't.

110
00:09:09.560 --> 00:09:11.119
No. you can.

111
00:09:11.120 --> 00:09:13.880
You-You have to.
Ray. I said no!

112
00:09:20.400 --> 00:09:21.600
OK. fine.

113
00:09:23.920 --> 00:09:25.280
It's your life.

114
00:09:27.640 --> 00:09:32.400
But. Rach. people.
they really need to know the truth.

115
00:09:35.680 --> 00:09:37.919
We've been shouting this
from the rooftops.

116
00:09:37.920 --> 00:09:40.799
Women are being stalked. spiked.

117
00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:42.479
First there was Flora Marshall.

118
00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:44.839
and now Charlie Downing
has been killed.

119
00:09:44.840 --> 00:09:48.199
What's next?
Sorry. Flora Marshall?

120
00:09:48.200 --> 00:09:52.999
She died last term
after an "alleged" overdose.

121
00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:54.559
"Alleged" overdose?

122
00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:56.719
That's what the uni trustees
want you to think.

123
00:09:56.720 --> 00:09:58.840
That's why people need us.
more than ever.

124
00:10:00.440 --> 00:10:01.600
Something's going on here.

125
00:10:02.680 --> 00:10:03.879
Something sinister.

126
00:10:03.880 --> 00:10:07.760
And no-one is listening.
I am.

127
00:10:09.360 --> 00:10:11.440
Show me what you've got.
I want to see it.

128
00:10:14.120 --> 00:10:15.560
I have evidence.

129
00:10:17.080 --> 00:10:19.720
Videos. People upload them
to our online portal.

130
00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:25.280
'I am walking home now.
pretty sure I'm being followed.'

131
00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:35.120
Another?

132
00:10:37.960 --> 00:10:41.439
'Just seen someone wearing
a uni hoody pulled over their face.

133
00:10:41.440 --> 00:10:43.879
'They were looking at me
through the window. Oh...'

134
00:10:43.880 --> 00:10:45.679
Another?

135
00:10:45.680 --> 00:10:48.319
'Can you get
some water? I don't really know.'

136
00:10:48.320 --> 00:10:50.839
'What do you think happened?'
'Our friend's been spiked.

137
00:10:50.840 --> 00:10:53.759
'The ambulance is on its way.
so it's gonna be OK.

138
00:10:53.760 --> 00:10:55.280
'It's gonna be all right.'

139
00:10:57.400 --> 00:10:58.680
Do you believe me now?

140
00:11:00.800 --> 00:11:02.320
I believe you.

141
00:11:04.600 --> 00:11:06.760
Maddie. can you share these videos
with us?

142
00:11:07.960 --> 00:11:09.120
Sure.

143
00:11:11.200 --> 00:11:14.879
Charlie and I got on as housemates.
but we didn't hang out that much.

144
00:11:14.880 --> 00:11:19.079
Any tensions? Conflicts with anyone?
Other than her boyfriend. you mean?

145
00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:21.760
Did she argue with her boyfriend
a lot? Yeah.

146
00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:25.519
Last night. I...

147
00:11:25.520 --> 00:11:28.639
I don't know what about. but she
was supposed to be staying at his.

148
00:11:28.640 --> 00:11:30.839
Then she texted to say
she was on her way home

149
00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:33.079
cos they'd had a row.
Do you know her boyfriend's name?

150
00:11:33.080 --> 00:11:34.120
Tom Carlton.

151
00:11:35.240 --> 00:11:38.279
I never actually met him.
He never came over.

152
00:11:38.280 --> 00:11:40.359
He didn't like her living on campus.

153
00:11:40.360 --> 00:11:42.240
Is there anything else
we should be aware of?

154
00:11:43.440 --> 00:11:49.039
Well... there was this guy that came
to the flat once.

155
00:11:49.040 --> 00:11:51.759
I got home and could see them
from my window in the garden.

156
00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:54.519
He was... shouting at her.

157
00:11:54.520 --> 00:11:56.319
Did you know him?
No.

158
00:11:56.320 --> 00:11:58.600
I asked Charlie about him. but...

159
00:12:00.080 --> 00:12:01.439
...she went weird on me.

160
00:12:01.440 --> 00:12:04.879
To be honest. she'd been
super paranoid for months.

161
00:12:04.880 --> 00:12:06.840
kept thinking
she was being followed.

162
00:12:08.480 --> 00:12:11.079
Did she ever report it?
No. I told her to.

163
00:12:11.080 --> 00:12:13.759
Loads of women around campus
have been saying the same thing.

164
00:12:13.760 --> 00:12:16.239
that they're been followed
and watched.

165
00:12:16.240 --> 00:12:18.279
We're all scared to go out
on our own.

166
00:12:18.280 --> 00:12:21.119
Did you ever experience
anything like that?

167
00:12:21.120 --> 00:12:22.319
Personally. no.

168
00:12:22.320 --> 00:12:23.959
But...

169
00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:27.119
one night. I looked outside and...

170
00:12:27.120 --> 00:12:29.119
there was this man.

171
00:12:29.120 --> 00:12:32.719
He had a Sussex Met hoodie
pulled over his face.

172
00:12:32.720 --> 00:12:35.400
and he was just staring up
at Charlie's room.

173
00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:46.800
I'm sorry to have to ask you this.
Tom. I know it's very difficult.

174
00:12:48.480 --> 00:12:50.320
Were you with Charlie last night?

175
00:12:54.040 --> 00:12:57.119
No. I was on a late shift.

176
00:12:57.120 --> 00:12:59.759
I work at Juice'n'Bun.
The burger place.

177
00:12:59.760 --> 00:13:02.279
So when was the last time
you saw her?

178
00:13:02.280 --> 00:13:05.600
Earlier. She came over before uni.

179
00:13:07.960 --> 00:13:09.840
And how were things between you?

180
00:13:11.480 --> 00:13:12.799
Normal.

181
00:13:12.800 --> 00:13:15.120
No disagreements. or...?

182
00:13:16.440 --> 00:13:17.480
No.

183
00:13:19.200 --> 00:13:22.640
I meant to call her when I got home.
but I was shattered.

184
00:13:24.600 --> 00:13:26.080
That looks really sore.

185
00:13:27.240 --> 00:13:28.280
Oh.

186
00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:32.879
Yeah. A customer came in
last night pissed up.

187
00:13:32.880 --> 00:13:34.279
and I refused to serve him.

188
00:13:34.280 --> 00:13:36.240
But the chef wasn't very happy
about it. so...

189
00:13:37.800 --> 00:13:38.920
...got into a bit of a thing.

190
00:13:40.440 --> 00:13:41.640
It happens.

191
00:13:49.920 --> 00:13:51.400
I think I need to be alone now.

192
00:13:56.120 --> 00:13:57.560
Yeah. of course.

193
00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:06.479
DOOR CLOSES

194
00:14:06.480 --> 00:14:07.560
Where are you?

195
00:14:09.240 --> 00:14:10.920
We need to talk. Call me back.

196
00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:19.639
As we thought.
the cause of death is strangulation.

197
00:14:19.640 --> 00:14:22.399
She was likely deposited
in the river after death.

198
00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:26.919
We also found high levels
of Bromadiazapine in her system.

199
00:14:26.920 --> 00:14:29.919
What is that. a sedative?
Essentially. yes.

200
00:14:29.920 --> 00:14:33.999
Used for panic attacks.
anti-anxiety. alcohol withdrawal.

201
00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:36.359
It's prevalent in universities.

202
00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:38.399
Students are using it
recreationally.

203
00:14:38.400 --> 00:14:41.919
So she could have taken it herself?
It's unlikely.

204
00:14:41.920 --> 00:14:43.559
The levels are extremely high.

205
00:14:43.560 --> 00:14:46.199
and it was taken within an hour
of her death.

206
00:14:46.200 --> 00:14:48.159
There are no needle marks.

207
00:14:48.160 --> 00:14:51.160
It looks like
someone either made her take it...

208
00:14:52.400 --> 00:14:54.600
...or it was slipped into her drink.

209
00:14:55.720 --> 00:14:57.600
Any sign of sexual assault?

210
00:14:58.720 --> 00:14:59.760
None.

211
00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:04.680
So. what was the motivation
for the drugging?

212
00:15:07.080 --> 00:15:10.039
If Maddie's right in thinking
that Flora Marshall was spiked

213
00:15:10.040 --> 00:15:11.520
as well...

214
00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:14.800
...is this the beginning
of a pattern?

215
00:15:17.760 --> 00:15:20.039
Given we have reports
of a stalker on campus

216
00:15:20.040 --> 00:15:21.600
wearing a Sussex Met hoodie...

217
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:26.199
...is it possible
that this is our killer?

218
00:15:26.200 --> 00:15:28.679
Are we looking at someone on campus.

219
00:15:28.680 --> 00:15:31.080
or an outsider wearing the hoodie
as cover?

220
00:15:32.720 --> 00:15:35.039
Let's start with looking
through university records

221
00:15:35.040 --> 00:15:38.079
for complaints made
of predatory behaviour.

222
00:15:38.080 --> 00:15:40.679
Go through social media and
the videos that Maddie sent through

223
00:15:40.680 --> 00:15:41.759
from Action Vigilant.

224
00:15:41.760 --> 00:15:43.239
We're already looking into

225
00:15:43.240 --> 00:15:45.959
whether Bromadiazapine
is circulating on campus.

226
00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:47.119
It's prescription only.

227
00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:48.759
As well as what happened
between Charlie

228
00:15:48.760 --> 00:15:51.119
and the guy she argued with
at her flat.

229
00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:53.359
What do we have on
Charlie's movements last night?

230
00:15:53.360 --> 00:15:57.000
We've got her at 7:31pm
on Southlands Drive.

231
00:16:02.560 --> 00:16:05.520
No sign of intoxication.
And then here. on the next camera...

232
00:16:07.200 --> 00:16:09.479
...she's gone.
Disappeared completely.

233
00:16:09.480 --> 00:16:12.559
There's a 500-metre patch of road
that isn't covered by CCTV

234
00:16:12.560 --> 00:16:14.439
until she gets to this point.

235
00:16:14.440 --> 00:16:15.999
So could she have turned off?

236
00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:18.760
Maybe taken a shortcut?
There's no side roads there.

237
00:16:20.400 --> 00:16:23.359
It looks like she got into a car.
Yeah. but it's a busy road.

238
00:16:23.360 --> 00:16:26.679
So if she'd been forced into a car.
somebody would have noticed.

239
00:16:26.680 --> 00:16:29.679
Uniform already spoke to residents
and shop keepers.

240
00:16:29.680 --> 00:16:30.999
No-one saw anything.

241
00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:34.119
So maybe she got into the car
of her own free will...

242
00:16:34.120 --> 00:16:36.719
which means
she probably knew her killer.

243
00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:38.999
Nick. check all the cars
that drove down Southlands

244
00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:40.999
from 7:30pm.

245
00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:45.439
Look for any links to Charlie.
friends. housemates. teachers.

246
00:16:45.440 --> 00:16:48.599
more specifically. the boyfriend.
Tom Carlton.

247
00:16:48.600 --> 00:16:52.839
Sasha. her flatmate. said Charlie
and Tom argued last night.

248
00:16:52.840 --> 00:16:54.679
Their relationship was up and down.

249
00:16:54.680 --> 00:16:57.079
Let's check his alibi...

250
00:16:57.080 --> 00:16:59.919
see if he really got that scratch
on his neck at work.

251
00:16:59.920 --> 00:17:02.719
Yeah. And see if we can get hold
of his medical records.

252
00:17:02.720 --> 00:17:05.600
Does he have access
to Bromadiazapine?

253
00:17:07.720 --> 00:17:11.359
Look. just get me the money.
Come on. man. please?!

254
00:17:11.360 --> 00:17:14.799
No! Davey! Davey. listen to me. OK?
This stops right here.

255
00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:16.919
We go to the police.
we tell them the truth.

256
00:17:16.920 --> 00:17:18.359
It only gets worse.

257
00:17:18.360 --> 00:17:22.039
No. No way. man.
I'm not going back to prison.

258
00:17:22.040 --> 00:17:24.519
I'm not going back to prison.
not for anybody.

259
00:17:24.520 --> 00:17:25.560
'Davey?!'

260
00:17:42.080 --> 00:17:44.999
We're here. and we're listening.

261
00:17:45.000 --> 00:17:48.759
I believe I speak on behalf
of all the trustees when I say

262
00:17:48.760 --> 00:17:52.359
that we will do everything
in our power to support you.

263
00:17:52.360 --> 00:17:54.119
Why are you lying?
Maddie.

264
00:17:54.120 --> 00:17:56.199
No. I'm sorry.
but you standing there

265
00:17:56.200 --> 00:17:58.239
saying that you'll
"do everything in your power".

266
00:17:58.240 --> 00:18:00.199
well. that's bullshit. isn't it?

267
00:18:00.200 --> 00:18:02.679
It's within your power
to grant access

268
00:18:02.680 --> 00:18:05.119
to complaints
and misconduct allegations.

269
00:18:05.120 --> 00:18:07.959
To be transparent. Meanwhile.
there's a stalker on campus.

270
00:18:07.960 --> 00:18:09.919
and women are afraid
to leave their homes.

271
00:18:09.920 --> 00:18:11.479
but you CHOOSE to do nothing.

272
00:18:11.480 --> 00:18:14.479
What exactly have you got to hide?
My dad's an arse.

273
00:18:14.480 --> 00:18:20.639
We live in a country where you
are innocent until proven guilty.

274
00:18:20.640 --> 00:18:23.999
Last time I checked.
that was a very good thing.

275
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:27.479
Why don't you see. by turning your
lens on potentially innocent people.

276
00:18:27.480 --> 00:18:29.959
making false allegations.

277
00:18:29.960 --> 00:18:32.639
your little star chamber
is turning this university

278
00:18:32.640 --> 00:18:34.679
into a vigilante state.

279
00:18:34.680 --> 00:18:36.719
What would you prefer?
That we put up and shut up?

280
00:18:36.720 --> 00:18:38.680
No. That's not what he's saying.

281
00:18:39.960 --> 00:18:43.719
Witch hunts do not catch witches.

282
00:18:43.720 --> 00:18:47.919
Your actions are affecting your
fellow students. our reputation.

283
00:18:47.920 --> 00:18:49.439
Our intake numbers.
There it is.

284
00:18:49.440 --> 00:18:51.079
What you care about. Your numbers.

285
00:18:51.080 --> 00:18:53.119
Maddie. please.
No! What about us?

286
00:18:53.120 --> 00:18:54.959
That's what I...
We are under threat!

287
00:18:54.960 --> 00:18:57.119
A student has died! We are afraid!

288
00:18:57.120 --> 00:18:59.399
And when we come to you for answers.
we are dismissed.

289
00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:02.400
So either you find out what the hell
is going on here. or we will!

290
00:19:05.080 --> 00:19:07.479
Southlands Drive is the main route
in and out of campus

291
00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:09.199
for every student. teacher
and academic.

292
00:19:09.200 --> 00:19:11.479
so pretty much everyone
was driving along it last night.

293
00:19:11.480 --> 00:19:13.439
It's nothing out of the ordinary.

294
00:19:13.440 --> 00:19:15.959
I've also been digging
into Tom's background. and...

295
00:19:15.960 --> 00:19:17.439
he's had a bit of a rough start.

296
00:19:17.440 --> 00:19:19.719
He was suspended at 13
for cannabis usage.

297
00:19:19.720 --> 00:19:22.399
then at 14. he was placed
under a child protection plan

298
00:19:22.400 --> 00:19:24.479
after his teacher noticed bruising
on his body.

299
00:19:24.480 --> 00:19:27.759
It was the same school he went to
with Charlie. as it happens.

300
00:19:27.760 --> 00:19:30.879
Were they childhood sweethearts?
No. not according to the housemate.

301
00:19:30.880 --> 00:19:33.119
She said they've been together
for about three years.

302
00:19:33.120 --> 00:19:36.159
We also checked
Tom's medical records.

303
00:19:36.160 --> 00:19:38.519
No sign of Bromadiazapine.

304
00:19:38.520 --> 00:19:41.119
I've been looking
through Charlie's emails.

305
00:19:41.120 --> 00:19:42.800
She'd had a conflict with the uni...

306
00:19:44.040 --> 00:19:46.079
...so it looks like they cut off
her hardship fund

307
00:19:46.080 --> 00:19:48.159
a couple of months back.

308
00:19:48.160 --> 00:19:49.839
And then after that...

309
00:19:49.840 --> 00:19:53.799
there's an exchange of
emotional emails with Carl Orton.

310
00:19:53.800 --> 00:19:55.840
her criminal psychology lecturer.

311
00:19:57.320 --> 00:19:59.799
I need to swing by the office.

312
00:19:59.800 --> 00:20:04.319
wade through the latest avalanche
of posts from Action Vigilant.

313
00:20:04.320 --> 00:20:06.639
Well. I've got time tonight.
forward them on.

314
00:20:06.640 --> 00:20:08.559
I'll work through them.
You sure?

315
00:20:08.560 --> 00:20:12.359
That'd be... Well. thanks. Stephen.
I owe you.

316
00:20:12.360 --> 00:20:13.799
But I should say.

317
00:20:13.800 --> 00:20:15.879
with the complaints policy.
nothing changes.

318
00:20:15.880 --> 00:20:17.800
Strictly confidential. Yes?
Of course.

319
00:20:18.960 --> 00:20:22.799
Oh. and. Jon.
regarding Charlie Downing's death.

320
00:20:22.800 --> 00:20:24.879
keep me across everything.

321
00:20:24.880 --> 00:20:26.600
Any developments. I wanna know.

322
00:20:29.160 --> 00:20:31.439
The truth is.
I.. I threw her a bit of work.

323
00:20:31.440 --> 00:20:33.479
Admin stuff. mainly.

324
00:20:33.480 --> 00:20:35.519
Well. is that normal?

325
00:20:35.520 --> 00:20:38.040
To have your students working
for you? No.

326
00:20:39.440 --> 00:20:42.039
And maybe I shouldn't have done it.

327
00:20:42.040 --> 00:20:46.079
But I... I felt sorry for her.
I mean. stopping her hardship fund.

328
00:20:46.080 --> 00:20:47.719
that's not right. is it?

329
00:20:47.720 --> 00:20:49.759
You're just elbowing out
the poor kids.

330
00:20:49.760 --> 00:20:52.960
Why did they stop the fund?
I didn't ask.

331
00:20:55.280 --> 00:20:58.079
Charlie was very private.

332
00:20:58.080 --> 00:21:01.679
And she lost her parents young.
like I did. it makes you that way.

333
00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:04.759
I... I just didn't wanna pry.
You must have talked?

334
00:21:04.760 --> 00:21:07.679
Oh. we talked. Mainly about
the problems at this place.

335
00:21:07.680 --> 00:21:09.759
And you're with the students
on that. are you?

336
00:21:09.760 --> 00:21:11.919
Not every time...

337
00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:15.239
but with Flora Marshall.
the uni was right.

338
00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:17.759
You don't believe she was spiked?
No.

339
00:21:17.760 --> 00:21:21.119
We have no idea
how she got hold of those drugs.

340
00:21:21.120 --> 00:21:23.919
Listen. these kids are just scared.

341
00:21:23.920 --> 00:21:25.599
That's triggered the uni
to over react

342
00:21:25.600 --> 00:21:28.519
and issue a zero-tolerance policy.
which is wrong. in my opinion.

343
00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:30.759
Well. surely they're just trying
to protect students?

344
00:21:30.760 --> 00:21:32.680
Or criminalise them. more like.

345
00:21:34.640 --> 00:21:36.599
If the uni had done more
to protect them.

346
00:21:36.600 --> 00:21:38.080
I might not be talking to you now.

347
00:21:41.360 --> 00:21:42.680
Why stop that fund?

348
00:21:43.840 --> 00:21:46.440
I mean. she was bright.
clearly in need.

349
00:21:47.880 --> 00:21:51.560
Maybe she was taking drugs.
I mean. her boyfriend has a history.

350
00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:02.119
Boss.

351
00:22:02.120 --> 00:22:04.839
I've been going through
Flora Marshall's social media.

352
00:22:04.840 --> 00:22:07.439
and she had a boyfriend.
Joe Franklin.

353
00:22:07.440 --> 00:22:09.359
He's left a series
of angry messages.

354
00:22:09.360 --> 00:22:12.919
accusing Charlie of causing Flora's
death. saying someone needs to pay.

355
00:22:12.920 --> 00:22:16.199
He also messaged Charlie directly.
calling her a heartless snake.

356
00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:18.199
She blocked him just after.

357
00:22:18.200 --> 00:22:20.079
So maybe the uni
stopped Charlie's funding.

358
00:22:20.080 --> 00:22:23.439
not because she was taking drugs.
but because she was dealing them?

359
00:22:23.440 --> 00:22:24.759
That would explain Joe's anger.

360
00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:28.119
Yeah. and that could be how
Charlie was funding her life.

361
00:22:28.120 --> 00:22:30.479
Bella. check Charlie's laptop
search history.

362
00:22:30.480 --> 00:22:32.399
look for online pharmacies.

363
00:22:32.400 --> 00:22:35.039
Boss... Tom's been lying to us.

364
00:22:35.040 --> 00:22:37.999
There was no altercation last night
because he wasn't even at work.

365
00:22:38.000 --> 00:22:39.679
According to one of the waitresses.

366
00:22:39.680 --> 00:22:41.799
he was out drinking
at The King and Queen pub.

367
00:22:41.800 --> 00:22:45.200
Hang on. Isn't that
at the top of Southlands Drive?

368
00:22:48.320 --> 00:22:50.799
Oh. yeah. Those two.

369
00:22:50.800 --> 00:22:53.359
I've seen them in here a few times.

370
00:22:53.360 --> 00:22:55.399
All over each other like a rash.

371
00:22:55.400 --> 00:22:56.879
They're normally no bother.

372
00:22:56.880 --> 00:22:59.320
but last night.
I had to chuck 'em out. Why?

373
00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:02.319
Were they being inappropriate?

374
00:23:02.320 --> 00:23:05.479
Not especially. no. To be fair.
they weren't the problem.

375
00:23:05.480 --> 00:23:07.479
It was the other fella.

376
00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:09.120
What other fella?

377
00:23:28.560 --> 00:23:31.000
Explains where Tom got
those scratches. Hm.

378
00:23:32.520 --> 00:23:37.360
Whoever that is. Tom knows him.
but why's he protecting him?

379
00:23:40.920 --> 00:23:41.960
Thanks for your help.

380
00:23:51.520 --> 00:23:53.320
CLATTERING

381
00:23:54.480 --> 00:23:55.640
Bronwyn?

382
00:24:20.400 --> 00:24:21.760
CAMERA CLICKS

383
00:24:31.280 --> 00:24:33.160
'Vee. it's your dad.

384
00:24:34.240 --> 00:24:37.079
'I know I've no right
to keep calling you. but. listen.

385
00:24:37.080 --> 00:24:39.839
'what you think you know about me.
the reason why I left...

386
00:24:39.840 --> 00:24:41.079
'none of it's true.

387
00:24:41.080 --> 00:24:43.919
'There's a mate of mine.
Dennis Tibson. in Eastville prison.

388
00:24:43.920 --> 00:24:45.479
'Talk to him.

389
00:24:45.480 --> 00:24:47.360
'There are things you need to know.'

390
00:24:52.160 --> 00:24:53.520
Nick.

391
00:24:54.720 --> 00:24:57.399
It looks like Roy's hunch was right.

392
00:24:57.400 --> 00:24:59.239
Charlie used a VPN to conceal it.

393
00:24:59.240 --> 00:25:01.839
but she's been buying
large quantities of Bromadiazapine

394
00:25:01.840 --> 00:25:03.679
from an online pharmacy.

395
00:25:03.680 --> 00:25:05.319
Well. I just checked.

396
00:25:05.320 --> 00:25:08.919
and Flora's death was also confirmed
as acute intoxication.

397
00:25:08.920 --> 00:25:10.440
attributed to Bromadiazapine.

398
00:25:11.600 --> 00:25:15.439
So. if Charlie sold the drugs
that caused Flora's death...

399
00:25:15.440 --> 00:25:16.760
did Joe retaliate?

400
00:25:29.600 --> 00:25:32.960
That's a nice hoodie. Joe.
It's my girlfriend's.

401
00:25:35.240 --> 00:25:36.719
I like the feel of it.

402
00:25:36.720 --> 00:25:39.160
I'm sorry about what happened
to Flora.

403
00:25:40.600 --> 00:25:44.239
You must be very angry.
I would be in your shoes.

404
00:25:44.240 --> 00:25:47.120
Is that why you sent
so many hate messages to Charlie?

405
00:25:48.080 --> 00:25:49.199
I told her the truth.

406
00:25:49.200 --> 00:25:51.960
If she hadn't been dealing.
Flora wouldn't have died.

407
00:25:53.640 --> 00:25:56.640
Least she could do was admit it.
But she didn't admit it. did she?

408
00:25:58.000 --> 00:26:00.039
Thanks to the uni.
she got away scot-free.

409
00:26:00.040 --> 00:26:02.479
There was no way of knowing
if Charlie sold drugs to Flora.

410
00:26:02.480 --> 00:26:04.160
We have a witness. Joe...

411
00:26:05.400 --> 00:26:07.759
...who saw someone
matching your description

412
00:26:07.760 --> 00:26:09.719
yelling at Charlie at her digs.

413
00:26:09.720 --> 00:26:11.039
That you?

414
00:26:11.040 --> 00:26:13.679
I need to go now.
What was the plan?

415
00:26:13.680 --> 00:26:16.720
Make her suffer
the way that Flora suffered? No.

416
00:26:18.120 --> 00:26:19.399
I wish I had.

417
00:26:19.400 --> 00:26:23.119
And last night. where were you?
I was at home.

418
00:26:23.120 --> 00:26:25.800
Can anyone vouch for that?
No.

419
00:26:27.280 --> 00:26:28.440
I was alone.

420
00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:32.120
Thanks to her. I'm always alone.

421
00:26:40.280 --> 00:26:42.000
See if we can verify his movements.

422
00:26:45.000 --> 00:26:48.240
After your brother. it's hard.
This must bring up a lot for you.

423
00:26:51.480 --> 00:26:53.280
Hey. Rach. How are you?

424
00:26:55.560 --> 00:26:56.640
I'm good.

425
00:26:57.920 --> 00:27:00.240
I-I'm not good actually.

426
00:27:01.520 --> 00:27:02.640
I hate this.

427
00:27:03.720 --> 00:27:05.560
She'd like those.

428
00:27:14.200 --> 00:27:17.160
This is why it's so important
you convince your dad.

429
00:27:19.080 --> 00:27:20.480
This can never happen again.

430
00:28:24.800 --> 00:28:28.559
Boss. I've just had a positive ID
on the man from The King and Queen.

431
00:28:28.560 --> 00:28:32.199
His name's Davey Carlton.
Davey Carlton?

432
00:28:32.200 --> 00:28:34.119
Tom Carlton's brother. yeah.

433
00:28:34.120 --> 00:28:36.479
He just got released from prison
last week

434
00:28:36.480 --> 00:28:40.439
on licence for the attempted murder
of his step-father.

435
00:28:40.440 --> 00:28:42.479
And I just called
his probation officer.

436
00:28:42.480 --> 00:28:45.680
and she said that he seemed
a little on edge this morning.

437
00:28:47.240 --> 00:28:49.240
And apparently. last night.
he was with Charlie.

438
00:28:52.000 --> 00:28:53.440
Tell her we're on our way.

439
00:28:55.600 --> 00:28:57.479
Well. that's the thing.

440
00:28:57.480 --> 00:28:59.479
Charlie was
Davey's girlfriend first.

441
00:28:59.480 --> 00:29:02.199
He was crazy about her.
They were childhood sweethearts.

442
00:29:02.200 --> 00:29:06.039
And then when he went to prison.
she turned to Tom for support.

443
00:29:06.040 --> 00:29:07.639
and it developed
into something more.

444
00:29:07.640 --> 00:29:11.599
Did Davey know about that?
Not until last night.

445
00:29:11.600 --> 00:29:14.119
And when you saw Davey. how was he?

446
00:29:14.120 --> 00:29:16.560
Hmm... Withdrawn.

447
00:29:17.960 --> 00:29:19.000
Depressed.

448
00:29:20.280 --> 00:29:21.999
I suggested that he speak
to his doctor

449
00:29:22.000 --> 00:29:24.119
about upping his anti-anxiety meds.

450
00:29:24.120 --> 00:29:26.759
What meds was he on?

451
00:29:26.760 --> 00:29:31.479
Citropram for depression.
and Bromadiazapine for anxiety.

452
00:29:31.480 --> 00:29:33.000
Bromadiazapine?
Mm-hm.

453
00:29:34.960 --> 00:29:38.679
Do you know when he last collected
his prescription?

454
00:29:38.680 --> 00:29:40.919
No. You'd have to speak
to his doctor about that.

455
00:29:40.920 --> 00:29:44.759
And Davey's relationship with Tom.
how was that?

456
00:29:44.760 --> 00:29:46.679
Prior to the altercation.

457
00:29:46.680 --> 00:29:48.799
Close. Inseparably close.

458
00:29:48.800 --> 00:29:51.239
I mean. Tom was his older brother.
his protector.

459
00:29:51.240 --> 00:29:54.079
He would've given his life for him.
Very nearly did. in fact.

460
00:29:54.080 --> 00:29:56.200
What do you mean?
Well...

461
00:29:57.400 --> 00:30:00.079
...before Davey was convicted
of attempted murder.

462
00:30:00.080 --> 00:30:01.359
Tom confessed.

463
00:30:01.360 --> 00:30:02.840
Tried to take the rap for him.

464
00:30:04.520 --> 00:30:07.079
Their step-father was hit over
the head with a cricket bat.

465
00:30:07.080 --> 00:30:08.399
and Tom claimed. falsely.

466
00:30:08.400 --> 00:30:10.799
that he was the one
who carried out the attack.

467
00:30:10.800 --> 00:30:12.519
Then. what changed?

468
00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:15.359
Children's services
had referred Tom to a therapist

469
00:30:15.360 --> 00:30:18.239
when he was a teenager
as part of his support programme.

470
00:30:18.240 --> 00:30:20.359
And he'd kept up the sessions
and he. well.

471
00:30:20.360 --> 00:30:23.880
he told his therapist the truth.
that Davey had swung the bat.

472
00:30:25.120 --> 00:30:28.559
He had presumed that
it was confidential. wrongly.

473
00:30:28.560 --> 00:30:31.119
And the therapist went
to the police? Yeah.

474
00:30:31.120 --> 00:30:32.680
As was his duty of care.

475
00:30:34.040 --> 00:30:36.239
Davey was arrested
the following morning.

476
00:30:36.240 --> 00:30:39.479
And they found specks of the
step-father's blood on his trainers.

477
00:30:39.480 --> 00:30:41.959
He eventually admitted it.

478
00:30:41.960 --> 00:30:44.279
and he was handed
a four-year custodial.

479
00:30:44.280 --> 00:30:46.319
How did Tom take that?

480
00:30:46.320 --> 00:30:49.279
He lost it in court.

481
00:30:49.280 --> 00:30:54.159
Started shouting threats
at the therapist. the judge. police.

482
00:30:54.160 --> 00:30:55.919
Had to be escorted out by security.

483
00:30:55.920 --> 00:30:58.119
Look. the reason I tell you
all of this

484
00:30:58.120 --> 00:31:00.680
is that Tom would do anything
for his brother.

485
00:31:02.240 --> 00:31:05.160
If anyone's gonna lead you to him.
it's Tom.

486
00:31:08.600 --> 00:31:11.839
Nick. I need someone over
to Eastville Prison urgently.

487
00:31:11.840 --> 00:31:13.439
Speak to the prison doctor.

488
00:31:13.440 --> 00:31:18.039
'Find out when Davey Carlton was
last prescribed Bromadiazapine.'

489
00:31:18.040 --> 00:31:19.280
On it.

490
00:31:21.200 --> 00:31:22.600
I-I'll go.

491
00:31:24.440 --> 00:31:25.960
I just need a change of scene.

492
00:31:42.680 --> 00:31:44.279
Thank you.

493
00:31:44.280 --> 00:31:47.239
Davey's been on Bromadiazapine
since he was a teenager.

494
00:31:47.240 --> 00:31:49.639
At one point.
he stopped taking it abruptly.

495
00:31:49.640 --> 00:31:52.199
which caused
a severe withdrawal reaction.

496
00:31:52.200 --> 00:31:54.639
It was restarted.
under close supervision.

497
00:31:54.640 --> 00:31:56.239
and he's been fine on it ever since.

498
00:31:56.240 --> 00:31:59.559
And when he stopped taking it.
what were the effects of that?

499
00:31:59.560 --> 00:32:03.760
An altered mental state.
aggression. confusion. rage.

500
00:32:04.920 --> 00:32:08.199
We put him in Care and Separation
for his own safety.

501
00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:10.240
He was there for over 80 days.

502
00:32:12.680 --> 00:32:14.319
Is there anything else?

503
00:32:14.320 --> 00:32:18.440
Actually. I'd. er...
like to speak to an inmate.

504
00:32:19.480 --> 00:32:20.680
Dennis Tibson.

505
00:32:30.600 --> 00:32:32.560
'I'm looking for information
on James Vernon.'

506
00:32:33.960 --> 00:32:37.199
You worked with him... at the Met?

507
00:32:37.200 --> 00:32:39.239
And you are?

508
00:32:39.240 --> 00:32:40.920
An ex-colleague of Vernon's.

509
00:32:43.040 --> 00:32:45.840
And this man? Do you remember him?

510
00:32:51.320 --> 00:32:53.359
Dave Cripps.

511
00:32:53.360 --> 00:32:54.440
I remember.

512
00:32:56.200 --> 00:32:57.760
Why did Vernon leave London?

513
00:32:58.880 --> 00:33:01.280
There was an informant at the time
who vanished.

514
00:33:02.920 --> 00:33:05.679
Word was it was Vernon's doing.

515
00:33:05.680 --> 00:33:07.399
Vernon murdered him?

516
00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:08.880
That's what people said.

517
00:33:10.360 --> 00:33:12.279
Didn't help that Cripps stayed
in situ.

518
00:33:12.280 --> 00:33:15.799
fanning the flames. until everyone
was convinced that he'd done it.

519
00:33:15.800 --> 00:33:18.959
Everyone apart from me. that is.
You didn't believe it?

520
00:33:18.960 --> 00:33:20.400
It didn't sit right.

521
00:33:21.560 --> 00:33:24.640
Trust me. Cripps isn't a man
to make an enemy of.

522
00:33:28.400 --> 00:33:29.800
But I knew Vernon.

523
00:33:31.680 --> 00:33:32.840
He was a good man.

524
00:33:34.440 --> 00:33:36.119
And more than that...

525
00:33:36.120 --> 00:33:39.120
he had a daughter who he idolised.

526
00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:41.759
You're very young. aren't you.

527
00:33:41.760 --> 00:33:43.840
to have been a colleague
of Vernon's?

528
00:33:46.920 --> 00:33:48.480
Your dad told me you might come.

529
00:33:50.520 --> 00:33:51.799
Look...

530
00:33:51.800 --> 00:33:55.000
I don't know
what exactly he's caught up in...

531
00:33:56.000 --> 00:33:57.839
...but I promise you this.

532
00:33:57.840 --> 00:34:00.119
He wouldn't surface
unless he had to.

533
00:34:00.120 --> 00:34:02.080
And if Cripps is involved...

534
00:34:03.600 --> 00:34:06.720
...I'd say your dad is
in a whole world of trouble.

535
00:34:11.480 --> 00:34:13.000
I'm sorry. I have to go.

536
00:34:33.760 --> 00:34:34.840
The thing is...

537
00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:39.080
...I'm looking at your daughter
right now.

538
00:34:40.840 --> 00:34:42.559
She's a busy girl.

539
00:34:42.560 --> 00:34:44.359
'Don't push me. Cripps.

540
00:34:44.360 --> 00:34:47.120
'You touch her.
and you know what I'll do.'

541
00:34:48.680 --> 00:34:50.920
You can put a stop to this
any time you want. James.

542
00:34:52.600 --> 00:34:54.000
You just give me what I need.

543
00:35:12.080 --> 00:35:13.120
What?

544
00:35:14.240 --> 00:35:17.280
Just the way you shut down
my dad earlier. It was funny.

545
00:35:21.520 --> 00:35:23.040
PHONE CHIMES

546
00:35:24.640 --> 00:35:25.760
Noah.

547
00:35:30.560 --> 00:35:33.119
Who is it?

548
00:35:33.120 --> 00:35:34.400
It's anonymous.

549
00:35:37.840 --> 00:35:39.200
Yeah?

550
00:35:48.160 --> 00:35:51.160
Roy. got something from uniform.

551
00:35:52.880 --> 00:35:55.839
It's a doorbell cam
showing a car following Charlie

552
00:35:55.840 --> 00:35:58.519
down Southlands Drive last night.

553
00:35:58.520 --> 00:35:59.999
Run a check on the car's ownership.

554
00:36:00.000 --> 00:36:02.159
and it's recently been switched
to Davey.

555
00:36:02.160 --> 00:36:04.599
Looks like he bought it
just as he came out of prison.

556
00:36:04.600 --> 00:36:06.079
So he has a history of violence.

557
00:36:06.080 --> 00:36:09.960
access to Bromadiazapine.
and he followed Charlie last night.

558
00:36:12.120 --> 00:36:13.920
We've got more than enough
to arrest him.

559
00:36:19.480 --> 00:36:21.399
Vee. you had a phone call.

560
00:36:21.400 --> 00:36:24.319
You left your sunglasses
at Eastville Prison...

561
00:36:24.320 --> 00:36:26.760
while visiting an inmate?

562
00:36:27.960 --> 00:36:29.960
OK. Thanks. Bella.

563
00:36:31.560 --> 00:36:33.480
Noah!

564
00:36:39.160 --> 00:36:40.360
Who's Davey Carlton?

565
00:36:41.400 --> 00:36:42.640
No idea.

566
00:36:44.520 --> 00:36:45.680
Hm.

567
00:37:47.240 --> 00:37:49.520
No sign that Davey's been here.
but...

568
00:37:50.520 --> 00:37:54.800
...we did find almost two grand
in cash.

569
00:37:58.680 --> 00:38:00.239
You're barking up the wrong tree.

570
00:38:00.240 --> 00:38:02.879
You know. if I thought that Davey
had touched one hair on her head.

571
00:38:02.880 --> 00:38:05.120
I wouldn't think twice.
I'd give him up.

572
00:38:06.800 --> 00:38:07.920
Would you. Tom?

573
00:38:09.880 --> 00:38:12.239
Because when we asked you about
the scratch on your neck.

574
00:38:12.240 --> 00:38:14.679
you lied
to cover for your brother.

575
00:38:14.680 --> 00:38:17.760
Just like you lied to cover for him
when he attacked your step-father.

576
00:38:18.920 --> 00:38:22.519
That was different.
Was it? How?

577
00:38:22.520 --> 00:38:26.080
That sadistic bastard tortured us...
for years.

578
00:38:27.280 --> 00:38:30.039
Davey snapped.
Another day. that would've been me.

579
00:38:30.040 --> 00:38:32.519
I hear if the therapist had
stayed quiet. you'd be in prison.

580
00:38:32.520 --> 00:38:36.079
But he didn't keep quiet. did he?
Davey served the time.

581
00:38:36.080 --> 00:38:37.720
Do you feel guilty about that?

582
00:38:39.520 --> 00:38:41.160
I didn't want him to suffer...

583
00:38:43.240 --> 00:38:44.560
...any more than he already had.

584
00:38:45.960 --> 00:38:48.039
And prison changes people.
doesn't it?

585
00:38:48.040 --> 00:38:51.119
Is that what the nest egg was for.
to give him a fresh start?

586
00:38:51.120 --> 00:38:52.399
It's none of your business.

587
00:38:52.400 --> 00:38:55.280
It is my business
if it's profit from drugs.

588
00:38:56.720 --> 00:38:59.199
Look. we know Charlie was dealing.

589
00:38:59.200 --> 00:39:02.959
Were you dealing too. Tom?
Are you kidding me?

590
00:39:02.960 --> 00:39:06.639
I didn't wanna touch a single penny
of that money.

591
00:39:06.640 --> 00:39:10.039
I hated that she was doing it.
All to stay on that stupid course.

592
00:39:10.040 --> 00:39:13.319
To prove that she was good enough.
which was ridiculous.

593
00:39:13.320 --> 00:39:16.480
She was a world better
than all of those other parasites.

594
00:39:17.640 --> 00:39:21.640
OK. after the argument at the pub.
where did you go?

595
00:39:23.360 --> 00:39:26.799
I went to the beach.
I needed some air.

596
00:39:26.800 --> 00:39:29.999
And Davey?
He came here.

597
00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:32.960
Are you sure about that?
I'm sure.

598
00:39:36.400 --> 00:39:39.319
The CCTV images. That's your car.

599
00:39:39.320 --> 00:39:42.799
It was following Charlie
after she left the pub.

600
00:39:42.800 --> 00:39:45.320
Do you recognise the car. Tom?

601
00:39:50.920 --> 00:39:52.400
It's your brother's car. isn't it?

602
00:39:58.800 --> 00:40:01.360
Oh. you... you didn't know. did you?

603
00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:04.960
I'm sorry.

604
00:40:08.320 --> 00:40:10.240
Prison really does change people.

605
00:40:15.840 --> 00:40:17.599
Why aren't we seizing the money?

606
00:40:17.600 --> 00:40:20.759
For Davey to stay hidden.
he needs help. and he needs cash.

607
00:40:20.760 --> 00:40:24.559
And it's only a matter of time
before his brother gets it to him.

608
00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:26.919
Get Nick to keep an eye
on Tom Carlton.

609
00:40:26.920 --> 00:40:30.399
and let's ask Bella to check
the CCTV from the beach last night.

610
00:40:30.400 --> 00:40:32.520
Let's see
if he was telling the truth.

611
00:40:34.440 --> 00:40:36.879
All complaints are confidential.

612
00:40:36.880 --> 00:40:38.840
End of subject.
Yeah. but it's wrong!

613
00:40:39.880 --> 00:40:42.039
Why can't you just stand up
and do something for once?

614
00:40:42.040 --> 00:40:44.599
We know who killed Charlie.
What?

615
00:40:44.600 --> 00:40:48.159
We've had a tip off. Davey Carlton.
Her ex. We might post it.

616
00:40:48.160 --> 00:40:51.839
Maddie. emotions are running
very high at the moment.

617
00:40:51.840 --> 00:40:54.879
and any misinformation
will just inflame the situation.

618
00:40:54.880 --> 00:40:56.439
It's not misinformation.

619
00:40:56.440 --> 00:40:58.719
He's just been released from prison.
and now she's dead.

620
00:40:58.720 --> 00:41:00.719
Those are facts.
You've been warned

621
00:41:00.720 --> 00:41:02.519
to stay out of things
that don't concern you.

622
00:41:02.520 --> 00:41:04.519
But that's the problem.
They do concern me.

623
00:41:04.520 --> 00:41:06.799
You release that name.
and there will be consequences.

624
00:41:06.800 --> 00:41:09.279
Not just for students.
but for this entire city.

625
00:41:09.280 --> 00:41:11.920
Is that what you really want?
I don't know.

626
00:41:13.040 --> 00:41:14.160
Maybe it's what's needed.

627
00:41:16.840 --> 00:41:17.880
Roy...

628
00:41:19.160 --> 00:41:21.639
...we've got Tom on CCTV
down by the pier.

629
00:41:21.640 --> 00:41:23.840
He was four miles away
when Charlie died.

630
00:41:25.560 --> 00:41:27.079
Anything on Joe Franklin?

631
00:41:27.080 --> 00:41:28.639
Also in the clear.

632
00:41:28.640 --> 00:41:30.119
He was spotted by several people

633
00:41:30.120 --> 00:41:32.999
close to his student house
across town.

634
00:41:33.000 --> 00:41:36.119
Boss... you need to see this.

635
00:41:36.120 --> 00:41:39.079
'Charlie was failed
by a system

636
00:41:39.080 --> 00:41:40.919
'that released this man
far too early.

637
00:41:40.920 --> 00:41:43.959
'just as students are being failed
by a university

638
00:41:43.960 --> 00:41:45.599
'that refuses to tell the truth!

639
00:41:45.600 --> 00:41:48.559
'That refuses to listen.
I have had enough.

640
00:41:48.560 --> 00:41:49.999
'We have had enough.

641
00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:51.039
'I am calling on all of you

642
00:41:51.040 --> 00:41:53.719
'to share any information
that you might have.

643
00:41:53.720 --> 00:41:55.639
'Tell it to us at Action Vigilant.

644
00:41:55.640 --> 00:41:58.279
'Together. we can find Davey.

645
00:41:58.280 --> 00:42:02.359
'And together.
we can get justice for Charlie!'

646
00:42:02.360 --> 00:42:06.279
'Justice for Charlie.

647
00:42:06.280 --> 00:42:09.520
'Justice for Charlie!'

648
00:42:13.520 --> 00:42:15.200
Who the hell tipped them off?

649
00:42:16.960 --> 00:42:18.559
OK. we need to step this up.

650
00:42:18.560 --> 00:42:22.559
I'm not having this investigation
hijacked by misinformation

651
00:42:22.560 --> 00:42:25.000
and online speculation.

652
00:42:26.280 --> 00:42:27.439
Call a press conference.

653
00:42:27.440 --> 00:42:31.200
'We're doing everything in our power
to locate this man...

654
00:42:32.680 --> 00:42:33.800
'..Davey Carlton.

655
00:42:35.200 --> 00:42:38.559
'Caucasian. six foot.
last seen wearing blue jeans.

656
00:42:38.560 --> 00:42:40.840
'a blue hoodie and a grey jacket.

657
00:42:43.360 --> 00:42:45.839
'People are upset.
now. I understand that.

658
00:42:45.840 --> 00:42:48.159
'But I have to reiterate that

659
00:42:48.160 --> 00:42:52.279
'even though Davey Carlton
remains a person of interest.

660
00:42:52.280 --> 00:42:55.240
'he has not yet been charged
or proven guilty.

661
00:42:56.320 --> 00:42:59.879
'No-one should have to face justice
at the hands of the public.

662
00:42:59.880 --> 00:43:03.840
'Please... let us do our job.
Thank you.'

663
00:43:14.640 --> 00:43:15.720
Davey?

664
00:43:19.280 --> 00:43:20.320
Davey!

665
00:43:34.800 --> 00:43:36.520
PHONE CHIMES

666
00:44:04.200 --> 00:44:07.519
DOOR SLAMS.
CHATTER

667
00:44:07.520 --> 00:44:10.319
PASSER-BY 1: ..something I might
have done. it's been misconstrued.

668
00:44:10.320 --> 00:44:12.040
PASSER-BY 2: Misconstrued?
Stop! Stop!

669
00:44:15.080 --> 00:44:17.240
Davey. where are you?
You know. call me!

670
00:45:01.760 --> 00:45:03.639
Boss. I've found Davey's hideout.

671
00:45:03.640 --> 00:45:05.159
All his stuff's here.

672
00:45:05.160 --> 00:45:07.799
but I've looked everywhere.
and he is MIA.

673
00:45:07.800 --> 00:45:10.800
'Stay in position.
Report back the second he shows up.'

674
00:45:35.000 --> 00:45:36.720
Maddie.

675
00:45:49.760 --> 00:45:53.599
Time of death - between 8pm and 9pm.

676
00:45:53.600 --> 00:45:56.959
The cause of death's strangulation.
Same as Charlie.

677
00:45:56.960 --> 00:46:01.839
And we've found Maddie's
phone and laptop in the microwave.

678
00:46:01.840 --> 00:46:04.199
Then why not just take them?

679
00:46:04.200 --> 00:46:06.479
Let's get Forensics
to work their magic.

680
00:46:06.480 --> 00:46:07.759
She was exposing people.

681
00:46:07.760 --> 00:46:11.160
That alone must have made her
a lot of enemies. Yeah.

682
00:46:12.200 --> 00:46:14.359
And then there's Davey Carlton.

683
00:46:14.360 --> 00:46:17.799
Maddie just openly accused him
of murder on social media.

684
00:46:17.800 --> 00:46:20.799
Yeah. and Nick said that he wasn't
at his hideout all night.

685
00:46:20.800 --> 00:46:23.039
He could've gotten in easily.
Let's check the cameras.

686
00:46:23.040 --> 00:46:25.280
See who got in
between eight and nine last night.

687
00:46:28.840 --> 00:46:32.039
The window was already smashed.
so I went and got some help.

688
00:46:32.040 --> 00:46:33.600
Noah?

689
00:46:37.440 --> 00:46:40.999
Look. I'm... I'm sorry
to have to ask you this right now.

690
00:46:41.000 --> 00:46:44.799
but who knew Maddie would've been
working there last night?

691
00:46:44.800 --> 00:46:46.480
Pretty much everyone.

692
00:46:49.440 --> 00:46:50.880
"My light's always on."

693
00:46:51.920 --> 00:46:53.120
That's what she used to say.

694
00:46:54.160 --> 00:46:56.240
Do you know if anyone saw anything?

695
00:46:59.400 --> 00:47:01.600
Our lecturer. Carl Orton.

696
00:47:02.880 --> 00:47:04.000
His office is up there.

697
00:47:05.120 --> 00:47:06.479
He might have seen something.

698
00:47:06.480 --> 00:47:10.879
And given the appeal that Maddie
put out for information on Charlie.

699
00:47:10.880 --> 00:47:14.919
was she sent anything
that might have put her at risk?

700
00:47:14.920 --> 00:47:16.280
Everything put her at risk.

701
00:47:17.760 --> 00:47:20.400
There are a lot of people
who wanted her silenced.

702
00:47:21.680 --> 00:47:23.079
My dad included.

703
00:47:23.080 --> 00:47:26.280
Your dad is a trustee here.
is that right?

704
00:47:27.480 --> 00:47:28.640
Yeah.

705
00:47:31.040 --> 00:47:32.480
He used to be psychologist.

706
00:47:33.520 --> 00:47:35.120
And when my brother died.
he gave it up.

707
00:47:40.160 --> 00:47:41.839
Roy?

708
00:47:41.840 --> 00:47:45.040
I'm very sorry...
about your brother.

709
00:47:48.160 --> 00:47:49.480
Yeah. I'll see you in a minute.

710
00:47:50.840 --> 00:47:52.119
I'll leave you with this -

711
00:47:52.120 --> 00:47:56.039
Solzhenitsyn said that
"the line separating good and evil

712
00:47:56.040 --> 00:47:58.159
"passes through every human heart".

713
00:47:58.160 --> 00:47:59.600
What did he mean?

714
00:48:01.040 --> 00:48:06.919
He... He meant that duality exists
within all of us.

715
00:48:06.920 --> 00:48:09.439
and those who believe
that they are free of evil

716
00:48:09.440 --> 00:48:12.240
are perhaps
the most susceptible to it.

717
00:48:13.440 --> 00:48:15.760
Thank you. and have a great day.

718
00:48:17.920 --> 00:48:21.479
Carl. the window in your office.

719
00:48:21.480 --> 00:48:24.879
that gives you a clear view
to Action Vigilant. right?

720
00:48:24.880 --> 00:48:28.319
Yes. although.
I-I wasn't teaching last night.

721
00:48:28.320 --> 00:48:30.360
I left 6pm sharp.

722
00:48:32.160 --> 00:48:33.200
Oh. God.

723
00:48:34.800 --> 00:48:36.320
I can't quite believe it.

724
00:48:37.800 --> 00:48:39.720
Maddie was unique.

725
00:48:41.240 --> 00:48:42.480
Special.

726
00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:46.600
Look. the world needed
more young women like her.

727
00:48:54.760 --> 00:48:55.999
Vee. go ahead.

728
00:48:56.000 --> 00:48:58.279
'It looks like
Maddie was making serious inroads

729
00:48:58.280 --> 00:48:59.519
'into the campus stalker.'

730
00:48:59.520 --> 00:49:03.239
42 freedom of information requests
to the board of trustees.

731
00:49:03.240 --> 00:49:04.839
'All denied.

732
00:49:04.840 --> 00:49:07.319
'And she's been contacting
Stephen Welling.

733
00:49:07.320 --> 00:49:08.919
'asking him to release the file

734
00:49:08.920 --> 00:49:10.839
'on a complaint made
by a former student.'

735
00:49:10.840 --> 00:49:12.719
Freya Rollins.

736
00:49:12.720 --> 00:49:15.119
'But I'm not able to see
who the complaint is about

737
00:49:15.120 --> 00:49:17.079
'because the university's
redacted the name.'

738
00:49:17.080 --> 00:49:18.640
OK. good work. Thanks. Vee.

739
00:49:20.280 --> 00:49:22.960
Why was Maddie looking
into that particular student now?

740
00:49:26.240 --> 00:49:28.440
Maybe she'd worked out
who the stalker is.

741
00:49:36.120 --> 00:49:37.600
Maddie...

742
00:49:40.520 --> 00:49:41.840
Y-Your courage...

743
00:49:44.000 --> 00:49:45.680
...the way you fought for the truth.

744
00:49:50.040 --> 00:49:51.480
I'm gonna miss you...

745
00:49:53.280 --> 00:49:54.800
...so much.

746
00:50:00.440 --> 00:50:01.800
And whoever did this...

747
00:50:04.840 --> 00:50:07.039
...I've given the police access
to everything.

748
00:50:07.040 --> 00:50:08.440
'Make no mistake...

749
00:50:10.040 --> 00:50:11.440
'..they will find something.'

750
00:50:12.600 --> 00:50:13.880
They are coming for you.

751
00:50:21.520 --> 00:50:23.559
If we revealed the names of everyone

752
00:50:23.560 --> 00:50:25.159
who had a complaint made
against them.

753
00:50:25.160 --> 00:50:27.200
this place would erupt into chaos.

754
00:50:28.520 --> 00:50:30.239
One name. That's all I need.

755
00:50:30.240 --> 00:50:32.239
The student was called
Freya Rollins.

756
00:50:32.240 --> 00:50:34.879
I just need to know
who she made the complaint against.

757
00:50:34.880 --> 00:50:36.999
I understand that.
Detective Superintendent.

758
00:50:37.000 --> 00:50:39.879
I'm not being difficult.
it's just that...

759
00:50:39.880 --> 00:50:41.640
I've signed an NDA.

760
00:50:42.680 --> 00:50:46.239
What I can say is that there was
no concrete evidence against him.

761
00:50:46.240 --> 00:50:48.320
NDA's are irrelevant.

762
00:50:49.360 --> 00:50:51.559
Two students are dead.

763
00:50:51.560 --> 00:50:54.319
Now. we can do this the easy way
or the hard way.

764
00:50:54.320 --> 00:50:56.080
You tell me. or I get a warrant.

765
00:51:00.400 --> 00:51:03.159
I spoke to Jon Hammond.
the secretary.

766
00:51:03.160 --> 00:51:06.599
He claims he can't do anything
without the board's sign off.

767
00:51:06.600 --> 00:51:08.439
Stephen Welling's
not budging either.

768
00:51:08.440 --> 00:51:09.919
We're gonna need a warrant.

769
00:51:09.920 --> 00:51:12.679
PHONE BUZZES

770
00:51:12.680 --> 00:51:13.839
Go ahead. Nick.

771
00:51:13.840 --> 00:51:15.719
'I've got eyes
on Davey Carlton.

772
00:51:15.720 --> 00:51:18.119
'Get a team to the museum
on Alexander Street.'

773
00:51:18.120 --> 00:51:20.239
Good work. Keep him in sight.

774
00:51:20.240 --> 00:51:21.519
Roy?

775
00:51:21.520 --> 00:51:24.119
The DNA results are back
on the scratch on Charlie's face.

776
00:51:24.120 --> 00:51:26.000
They're a match for Davey.

777
00:52:21.680 --> 00:52:23.279
Stop! Police!

778
00:52:23.280 --> 00:52:24.600
You're not going anywhere!

779
00:52:39.080 --> 00:52:40.520
Hello. Davey.

780
00:52:43.480 --> 00:52:45.000
Tell me about Tuesday night.

781
00:52:46.200 --> 00:52:47.239
You'd just found out

782
00:52:47.240 --> 00:52:50.479
that Charlie was having
a relationship with your brother.

783
00:52:50.480 --> 00:52:51.720
That must have hurt.

784
00:52:53.840 --> 00:52:55.120
You think?

785
00:52:56.880 --> 00:52:59.599
Is that why you'd followed her
to the pub?

786
00:52:59.600 --> 00:53:01.040
How did you know she was there?

787
00:53:03.280 --> 00:53:04.400
I didn't.

788
00:53:05.840 --> 00:53:08.720
That's my brother's local.
I was looking for him.

789
00:53:10.240 --> 00:53:12.119
But you did follow her home.

790
00:53:12.120 --> 00:53:13.640
Why?

791
00:53:15.600 --> 00:53:16.720
I don't know.

792
00:53:17.960 --> 00:53:19.799
I was upset.

793
00:53:19.800 --> 00:53:21.640
I wanted to talk to her. ju...

794
00:53:22.800 --> 00:53:24.439
...just to talk.

795
00:53:24.440 --> 00:53:27.080
And then what happened?
Did you force her into your car?

796
00:53:28.880 --> 00:53:30.079
No.

797
00:53:30.080 --> 00:53:34.920
Well. your DNA was found
in a scratch on her face.

798
00:53:36.800 --> 00:53:40.120
How do you account for that?
It's why I ran.

799
00:53:42.920 --> 00:53:44.320
Look. me and Tom. we...

800
00:53:45.920 --> 00:53:48.439
...we got into a fight
in the car park.

801
00:53:48.440 --> 00:53:50.360
Charlie tried to stop us.

802
00:53:52.400 --> 00:53:54.080
Got in the middle.
and I scratched her.

803
00:53:55.400 --> 00:53:57.960
I didn't mean to.
I just caught her accidentally.

804
00:53:59.960 --> 00:54:01.799
I was angry.

805
00:54:01.800 --> 00:54:07.000
Really. really angry.
but I... I didn't kill her.

806
00:54:11.960 --> 00:54:13.840
Talk to me about Maddie Coleman.

807
00:54:18.120 --> 00:54:19.720
I didn't know her. She...

808
00:54:21.760 --> 00:54:23.120
She thought she knew me. though.

809
00:54:24.920 --> 00:54:26.559
Like everyone does.

810
00:54:26.560 --> 00:54:28.039
Well. that must have made you angry.

811
00:54:28.040 --> 00:54:30.239
her splashing your name
all over social media.

812
00:54:30.240 --> 00:54:31.680
calling for your arrest?

813
00:54:35.600 --> 00:54:37.200
Where were you last night?

814
00:54:38.720 --> 00:54:41.479
I was at the museum.
Oh. is that right?

815
00:54:41.480 --> 00:54:43.119
Cos one of our officers.
he had eyes on it.

816
00:54:43.120 --> 00:54:45.239
said you weren't there.

817
00:54:45.240 --> 00:54:46.720
Is he lying?

818
00:54:51.240 --> 00:54:52.640
I was at the river.

819
00:54:55.360 --> 00:54:56.799
It's quiet there.

820
00:54:56.800 --> 00:54:58.959
Can hear myself think.

821
00:54:58.960 --> 00:55:01.480
In prison. the noise...

822
00:55:05.040 --> 00:55:06.080
The river.

823
00:55:07.720 --> 00:55:10.240
Is that where you dumped
Charlie's body?

824
00:55:12.440 --> 00:55:14.080
I didn't kill her.

825
00:55:16.560 --> 00:55:17.920
I loved her.

826
00:55:21.800 --> 00:55:23.119
Hold him.

827
00:55:23.120 --> 00:55:26.239
Let's see if we can verify his story
about his whereabouts last night.

828
00:55:26.240 --> 00:55:29.000
Yeah.
Boss? You're gonna wanna see this.

829
00:55:31.720 --> 00:55:35.279
So. last night. Maddie sent
a video file to Carl Orton

830
00:55:35.280 --> 00:55:36.960
with a threat attached.

831
00:55:38.840 --> 00:55:41.639
Looks like the killer didn't do
as much damage to Maddie's devices

832
00:55:41.640 --> 00:55:42.959
as they'd hoped.

833
00:55:42.960 --> 00:55:45.159
Digital Forensics retrieved it.

834
00:55:45.160 --> 00:55:47.399
I just... I can't help it.

835
00:55:47.400 --> 00:55:50.279
I can't...
I can't stop thinking about you.

836
00:55:50.280 --> 00:55:51.519
And I know there's a...

837
00:55:51.520 --> 00:55:53.279
there's a special connection
between us.

838
00:55:53.280 --> 00:55:55.359
and I know that you feel it too.

839
00:55:55.360 --> 00:55:57.799
No. sorry. I don't...
Oh...

840
00:55:57.800 --> 00:56:00.399
I don't think
you should be talking like this.

841
00:56:00.400 --> 00:56:02.399
Come here.
No. I need to go.

842
00:56:02.400 --> 00:56:04.759
I said come here!
Just let me go!

843
00:56:04.760 --> 00:56:07.559
It's timestamped
to when Maddie sent it.

844
00:56:07.560 --> 00:56:09.839
We're still trying to figure out
when it was recorded.

845
00:56:09.840 --> 00:56:12.039
Two students dead...

846
00:56:12.040 --> 00:56:14.479
and another being assaulted
on camera.

847
00:56:14.480 --> 00:56:16.400
We need to identify the woman
in this video.

848
00:56:17.520 --> 00:56:19.400
Let's bring Carl Orton in.

849
00:56:41.720 --> 00:56:42.960
Mrs Orton...

850
00:56:44.040 --> 00:56:45.480
...is your husband home?

851
00:56:47.120 --> 00:56:50.119
No. not yet. Why?

852
00:56:50.120 --> 00:56:52.719
We have a warrant
to search the premises.

853
00:56:52.720 --> 00:56:54.320
We'll need to come in.

854
00:57:03.600 --> 00:57:05.760
Oh. come...
SHE SIGHS

855
00:57:08.240 --> 00:57:11.439
Look. please will somebody
just tell me what's going on?

856
00:57:11.440 --> 00:57:14.520
What's that up there?
That's Carl's dark room.

857
00:57:58.600 --> 00:57:59.800
Roy?

858
00:58:20.200 --> 00:58:21.480
Here.

859
00:59:03.800 --> 00:59:05.439
PHONE DIALS

860
00:59:05.440 --> 00:59:09.039
Vee. I'm sending you an image.
I need an ID.

861
00:59:09.040 --> 00:59:10.200
You shouldn't be in here.

862
00:59:13.680 --> 00:59:16.359
Carl Orton. you are under arrest

863
00:59:16.360 --> 00:59:19.040
for the murders of Charlie Downing
and Maddie Coleman.

864
00:59:50.880 --> 00:59:53.439
There's
a special connection between us.

865
00:59:53.440 --> 00:59:55.119
and I know that you feel it too.

866
00:59:55.120 --> 00:59:57.599
No. sorry. I don't...
Oh...

867
00:59:57.600 --> 00:59:59.879
I don't think
you should be talking like this.

868
00:59:59.880 --> 01:00:02.399
Come here.
No. I need to go.

869
01:00:02.400 --> 01:00:04.159
I said come here!
Just let me go!

870
01:00:04.160 --> 01:00:05.520
SHE GRUNTS

871
01:00:09.080 --> 01:00:10.280
Look. I'm sorry.

872
01:00:12.040 --> 01:00:14.759
I shouldn't have got grabby
with Rachel.

873
01:00:14.760 --> 01:00:18.759
You didn't "get grabby".
You attacked her.

874
01:00:18.760 --> 01:00:21.120
Yes. I overstepped the mark.

875
01:00:22.200 --> 01:00:23.679
Just the once.

876
01:00:23.680 --> 01:00:25.719
And it's... it's not how it seems.

877
01:00:25.720 --> 01:00:28.599
Maddie. she...
she edited the videos.

878
01:00:28.600 --> 01:00:30.280
Sh-She wanted to make me look bad.

879
01:00:31.440 --> 01:00:33.799
What about Freya Rollins?

880
01:00:33.800 --> 01:00:37.679
And all the students you stalked
and photographed without consent?

881
01:00:37.680 --> 01:00:39.919
Were they trying
to make you look bad as well?

882
01:00:39.920 --> 01:00:42.199
I've made mistakes. I admit it.

883
01:00:42.200 --> 01:00:44.960
But I-I didn't kill Maddie. I swear.

884
01:00:46.880 --> 01:00:48.920
Talk me through your movements
last night.

885
01:00:50.320 --> 01:00:52.159
OK. I...

886
01:00:52.160 --> 01:00:55.760
I left flowers at Rachel's flat.
earlier in the day...

887
01:00:57.000 --> 01:00:58.559
...to apologise.

888
01:00:58.560 --> 01:01:02.519
But I-I didn't hear from her.
so I went back last night.

889
01:01:02.520 --> 01:01:04.600
I just wanted to talk. that's all.

890
01:01:05.840 --> 01:01:07.599
But then her flatmate
wouldn't let me in.

891
01:01:07.600 --> 01:01:10.559
so I left a message saying
that I'd be in the office.

892
01:01:10.560 --> 01:01:13.279
I went back to the uni.
She didn't come.

893
01:01:13.280 --> 01:01:15.160
Why couldn't you have
just left her alone?

894
01:01:18.400 --> 01:01:21.839
The uni hoodie
we found in your darkroom...

895
01:01:21.840 --> 01:01:23.799
is that yours?

896
01:01:23.800 --> 01:01:26.559
It's lost property. that's all.

897
01:01:26.560 --> 01:01:28.599
And the Bromadiazapine?

898
01:01:28.600 --> 01:01:32.039
We found large quantities of it
in your drawer.

899
01:01:32.040 --> 01:01:33.800
It belonged to Charlie Downing.

900
01:01:34.880 --> 01:01:37.359
I found them on her
and confiscated them.

901
01:01:37.360 --> 01:01:39.039
I was just trying to help her.

902
01:01:39.040 --> 01:01:42.359
Well. I think
you like to control young women.

903
01:01:42.360 --> 01:01:44.959
Freya. then Charlie. now Rachel.

904
01:01:44.960 --> 01:01:48.479
You followed them.
you photographed them.

905
01:01:48.480 --> 01:01:50.120
you instilled fear in them.

906
01:01:51.160 --> 01:01:52.559
And you were getting away with it

907
01:01:52.560 --> 01:01:54.999
until Maddie came along
and discovered your secret.

908
01:01:55.000 --> 01:01:56.959
She was gonna expose you.
so you killed her.

909
01:01:56.960 --> 01:02:00.199
No... I-I swear.

910
01:02:00.200 --> 01:02:03.280
I swear on my unborn child.
I didn't.

911
01:02:09.080 --> 01:02:10.599
Bronwyn?

912
01:02:10.600 --> 01:02:12.799
If you're looking for Rachel.
she's out with her mum.

913
01:02:12.800 --> 01:02:13.919
Maybe you can help us.

914
01:02:13.920 --> 01:02:17.399
Did anyone come round here
last night. looking for Rachel?

915
01:02:17.400 --> 01:02:18.560
Carl Orton. you mean?

916
01:02:20.000 --> 01:02:21.600
Yeah. he did.

917
01:02:22.680 --> 01:02:24.320
Not that I let him
anywhere near her.

918
01:02:25.960 --> 01:02:27.759
Creep.

919
01:02:27.760 --> 01:02:30.159
Do you remember
what time that was?

920
01:02:30.160 --> 01:02:31.719
Yeah. it was like 8:40pm.

921
01:02:31.720 --> 01:02:34.159
Do you know what he wanted
to talk to her about?

922
01:02:34.160 --> 01:02:36.039
Well. from the way
that he was sweating.

923
01:02:36.040 --> 01:02:38.200
I'm guessing the video
that she took of him.

924
01:02:39.960 --> 01:02:42.919
Is she in trouble?
No. Not... Not at all.

925
01:02:42.920 --> 01:02:47.119
Carl's the one that's in trouble.
He's currently under arrest.

926
01:02:47.120 --> 01:02:49.279
Bronwyn.
why didn't she go to the uni

927
01:02:49.280 --> 01:02:51.199
or the police with that video?

928
01:02:51.200 --> 01:02:55.720
She was scared.
Carl's popular. isn't he?

929
01:02:57.400 --> 01:02:58.999
And in a position of power.

930
01:02:59.000 --> 01:03:01.639
And she knew
the uni probably wouldn't listen.

931
01:03:01.640 --> 01:03:03.719
whatever she said. so...

932
01:03:03.720 --> 01:03:08.039
her only shot at getting rid of him
was sending Maddie that video.

933
01:03:08.040 --> 01:03:10.599
Do you happen to remember
when she might've recorded it?

934
01:03:10.600 --> 01:03:14.119
Well. yeah. it was the night before
last. when Charlie was killed.

935
01:03:14.120 --> 01:03:16.320
Rachel called me. crying.
straight after.

936
01:03:17.560 --> 01:03:20.080
You've been very helpful. Thank you.
Thank you.

937
01:03:24.160 --> 01:03:28.159
If she's telling the truth.
we need to verify Carl's movements.

938
01:03:28.160 --> 01:03:30.599
And we need to see
Rachel's original video.

939
01:03:30.600 --> 01:03:33.439
I wanna check those timecodes.

940
01:03:33.440 --> 01:03:35.479
Videos are uploaded via a portal
on our website.

941
01:03:35.480 --> 01:03:37.039
so if Maddie wanted to post it.

942
01:03:37.040 --> 01:03:39.319
then. yeah.
she would have edited it down.

943
01:03:39.320 --> 01:03:40.719
That way the video loops

944
01:03:40.720 --> 01:03:42.879
and the algorithm sees
that we're getting more views

945
01:03:42.880 --> 01:03:45.119
and pushes it to more users.
It's just a standard thing.

946
01:03:45.120 --> 01:03:47.319
But I can see if I can get
the original for you?

947
01:03:47.320 --> 01:03:49.080
Please.

948
01:03:57.880 --> 01:04:00.920
Erm. I'm sorry. but it looks like
she permanently deleted it.

949
01:04:03.880 --> 01:04:05.399
I've been tracing Carl's movements.

950
01:04:05.400 --> 01:04:08.279
and I've got him
at the university car park at 9:15pm

951
01:04:08.280 --> 01:04:10.039
on his way out.

952
01:04:10.040 --> 01:04:14.199
So. if Carl didn't show up
at Rachel's until 8:40pm.

953
01:04:14.200 --> 01:04:16.919
and Maddie's time of death
was between 8pm and 9pm.

954
01:04:16.920 --> 01:04:19.199
does that give him enough time
to get back to the uni

955
01:04:19.200 --> 01:04:21.119
and then kill Maddie.
before leaving?

956
01:04:21.120 --> 01:04:23.879
Rachel's house is a good
ten. 15-minute drive to campus.

957
01:04:23.880 --> 01:04:25.080
OK.

958
01:04:26.320 --> 01:04:29.679
What about the night before last.
when Charlie died?

959
01:04:29.680 --> 01:04:33.119
We've got witnesses who saw Carl
and Rachel leaving a uni event

960
01:04:33.120 --> 01:04:34.439
at around 7:40.

961
01:04:34.440 --> 01:04:37.359
and later. there's an ANPR hit
near Rachel's house

962
01:04:37.360 --> 01:04:39.519
at the same time
that Charlie disappeared.

963
01:04:39.520 --> 01:04:41.840
It's too close in both cases.

964
01:04:43.080 --> 01:04:44.359
He's in the clear.

965
01:04:44.360 --> 01:04:47.319
Well. maybe he's not a killer.
but he's still a piece of work.

966
01:04:47.320 --> 01:04:48.719
He should be behind bars.

967
01:04:48.720 --> 01:04:50.239
OK. let's charge him with assault.

968
01:04:50.240 --> 01:04:53.120
but we're gonna have
to bail him for now.

969
01:04:54.160 --> 01:04:57.680
What I don't get is
why would Maddie delete that video?

970
01:04:58.720 --> 01:05:00.000
Maybe she didn't.

971
01:05:01.280 --> 01:05:04.360
What if someone's gone to great
lengths to frame Carl Orton?

972
01:05:05.920 --> 01:05:08.200
I think the answer lies
in that deleted footage.

973
01:05:09.760 --> 01:05:11.839
Is there something in that file

974
01:05:11.840 --> 01:05:13.799
that the killer
doesn't want us to see?

975
01:05:13.800 --> 01:05:15.840
Well. there has to be a way
of retrieving it.

976
01:05:30.160 --> 01:05:33.399
Stephen. I am so sorry. Let's...

977
01:05:33.400 --> 01:05:36.759
Er... Clear your desk. Carl.

978
01:05:36.760 --> 01:05:38.679
I want you out of here immediately.

979
01:05:38.680 --> 01:05:43.120
Do you have any idea of
the monumental damage you've done?

980
01:05:49.280 --> 01:05:50.959
Roy...

981
01:05:50.960 --> 01:05:53.479
Digital Forensics have retrieved
the extended footage

982
01:05:53.480 --> 01:05:55.040
from Action Vigilant's server.

983
01:05:57.240 --> 01:05:58.519
Here.

984
01:05:58.520 --> 01:05:59.880
Please stay away.

985
01:06:01.120 --> 01:06:03.599
Carl. no. no. no. no!
SHE PANTS

986
01:06:03.600 --> 01:06:05.719
Just... stop. Stop.
Stop. you're being...

987
01:06:05.720 --> 01:06:07.880
Stop! Please stop!
THUD

988
01:06:09.880 --> 01:06:11.959
This doesn't make sense.

989
01:06:11.960 --> 01:06:16.719
Maddie was about maximum impact.
hits. you know. creating a stir.

990
01:06:16.720 --> 01:06:19.120
There is no way
she would've edited out that attack.

991
01:06:21.520 --> 01:06:22.800
Play it again.

992
01:06:25.400 --> 01:06:27.040
I can't believe it.

993
01:06:28.520 --> 01:06:32.360
Carl Orton's been released.
I just saw him.

994
01:06:35.680 --> 01:06:37.760
He attacked me. Noah.

995
01:06:39.240 --> 01:06:40.679
He attacked you?

996
01:06:40.680 --> 01:06:42.599
I don't know what to do.

997
01:06:42.600 --> 01:06:44.360
This place. I...

998
01:06:45.400 --> 01:06:47.959
SHE BREATHES SHAKILY
I can't... I can't breathe.

999
01:06:47.960 --> 01:06:50.679
Hey. hey. hey.
Let's... Let's get out of here.

1000
01:06:50.680 --> 01:06:52.079
SHE SOBS

1001
01:06:52.080 --> 01:06:55.280
Let's go for a drive. Yeah?

1002
01:06:58.320 --> 01:07:01.839
'Please. please stay away.
No. no. no. no. Stop.

1003
01:07:01.840 --> 01:07:03.920
'Just stop. Stop. Please stop!'
There.

1004
01:07:06.600 --> 01:07:08.479
Zoom in.

1005
01:07:08.480 --> 01:07:09.760
Closer.

1006
01:07:12.000 --> 01:07:13.600
That's Charlie Downing.

1007
01:07:25.520 --> 01:07:27.480
That car belongs to Stephen Welling.

1008
01:07:30.120 --> 01:07:32.519
OK. check the registration
against all the cars

1009
01:07:32.520 --> 01:07:34.680
that were in the uni car park
last night.

1010
01:07:36.560 --> 01:07:39.200
Yeah. It was there.

1011
01:07:44.920 --> 01:07:48.240
We need to find Rachel
before Stephen Welling does.

1012
01:07:57.000 --> 01:07:59.119
The therapist who testified
against Davey in court

1013
01:07:59.120 --> 01:08:00.520
was Stephen Welling.

1014
01:08:01.680 --> 01:08:03.799
Apparently.
when Davey was sentenced.

1015
01:08:03.800 --> 01:08:07.679
Tom threatened
to destroy Stephen's family.

1016
01:08:07.680 --> 01:08:09.399
And a month later.
Alexander Welling.

1017
01:08:09.400 --> 01:08:11.999
Stephen's son. was murdered.

1018
01:08:12.000 --> 01:08:15.479
So. this is Alexander.

1019
01:08:15.480 --> 01:08:17.559
And this guy walking up here
in the blue hoodie

1020
01:08:17.560 --> 01:08:18.919
throws the punch.

1021
01:08:18.920 --> 01:08:20.760
CCTV didn't capture his face.

1022
01:08:23.520 --> 01:08:26.959
So there were a number of suspects.
Tom Carlton among them.

1023
01:08:26.960 --> 01:08:29.759
His build and height matched
witness descriptions of the attacker

1024
01:08:29.760 --> 01:08:32.759
and a similar hoodie was found
at his house.

1025
01:08:32.760 --> 01:08:35.359
But he was released
after questioning.

1026
01:08:35.360 --> 01:08:38.439
It looks like he was given an alibi
by Charlie Downing.

1027
01:08:38.440 --> 01:08:40.199
So it's possible
that Tom really did it

1028
01:08:40.200 --> 01:08:41.919
and Charlie lied to protect him?

1029
01:08:41.920 --> 01:08:44.559
If she did.
it certainly gives Stephen motive.

1030
01:08:44.560 --> 01:08:47.959
I've gone back over the list of cars
going up Southlands Drive

1031
01:08:47.960 --> 01:08:49.679
the night Charlie was murdered.

1032
01:08:49.680 --> 01:08:51.439
and Stephen's registration
is on there.

1033
01:08:51.440 --> 01:08:54.039
This could be a revenge attack.

1034
01:08:54.040 --> 01:08:56.640
And did Stephen kill
Charlie Downing?

1035
01:08:57.920 --> 01:08:59.879
Stephen kills Charlie Downing.

1036
01:08:59.880 --> 01:09:02.519
the person
who Tom and Davey loves the most.

1037
01:09:02.520 --> 01:09:05.040
in retaliation
for what happened to Alexander.

1038
01:09:06.440 --> 01:09:10.239
And when the video implicating
Stephen landed in Maddie's lap.

1039
01:09:10.240 --> 01:09:12.080
he was forced to kill her too.

1040
01:09:13.240 --> 01:09:15.919
And he knew that Carl
was the university stalker.

1041
01:09:15.920 --> 01:09:17.320
making him easy to frame.

1042
01:09:18.760 --> 01:09:21.599
The students are panicking.

1043
01:09:21.600 --> 01:09:25.959
We're being flooded with emails
from concerned parents.

1044
01:09:25.960 --> 01:09:30.359
Security on campus
needs an urgent review.

1045
01:09:30.360 --> 01:09:36.319
along with emergency procedures
and support services.

1046
01:09:36.320 --> 01:09:39.279
Right. I think
that we can all agree on that.

1047
01:09:39.280 --> 01:09:41.840
Thank you all very much
for your time. Thank you.

1048
01:09:45.600 --> 01:09:46.760
Roy?

1049
01:09:48.520 --> 01:09:50.639
Look. I've been going back over
Maddie's messages

1050
01:09:50.640 --> 01:09:52.399
the night that she died.

1051
01:09:52.400 --> 01:09:55.159
Apart from an email
about Freya Rollins.

1052
01:09:55.160 --> 01:09:57.999
there's none to
or from Stephen Welling.

1053
01:09:58.000 --> 01:10:00.359
So he had no way of knowing
that Maddie had that footage?

1054
01:10:00.360 --> 01:10:01.480
No.

1055
01:10:04.560 --> 01:10:06.000
Well. I'll tell you who did.

1056
01:10:08.200 --> 01:10:11.639
Her partner in crime. Noah.

1057
01:10:11.640 --> 01:10:15.359
Remember. he told us
that she deleted the video.

1058
01:10:15.360 --> 01:10:16.560
but why would she do that?

1059
01:10:17.680 --> 01:10:19.240
So you think Noah deleted it?

1060
01:10:20.560 --> 01:10:22.800
Maddie would have told him about it
when it came in.

1061
01:10:26.280 --> 01:10:29.439
If it was him
driving Stephen's car that night.

1062
01:10:29.440 --> 01:10:31.919
then he couldn't have risked
that footage getting out.

1063
01:10:31.920 --> 01:10:34.759
But... why would Charlie get
into a car with Noah?

1064
01:10:34.760 --> 01:10:36.960
Did she even know him?
Were they friends?

1065
01:10:44.400 --> 01:10:46.319
Yes.

1066
01:10:46.320 --> 01:10:47.920
They went to the same school.

1067
01:10:50.320 --> 01:10:52.120
PHONE BUZZES

1068
01:10:54.520 --> 01:10:55.679
Nick?

1069
01:10:55.680 --> 01:10:59.079
Stephen just confirmed
he hasn't used the car in weeks.

1070
01:10:59.080 --> 01:11:02.439
He says he lent it to his son.
'Yeah. we know. Noah.'

1071
01:11:02.440 --> 01:11:04.960
We need to find him.
We're gonna head to his flat.

1072
01:11:19.800 --> 01:11:21.040
It's so peaceful.

1073
01:11:22.320 --> 01:11:24.640
I used to come here all the time
when my brother died.

1074
01:11:26.800 --> 01:11:29.200
I'm really sorry about your...

1075
01:11:30.840 --> 01:11:31.880
Yeah.

1076
01:11:32.920 --> 01:11:34.200
Thanks. Rach.

1077
01:11:36.600 --> 01:11:39.760
I could've hugged you
when I saw that post.

1078
01:11:41.720 --> 01:11:45.320
It was such a relief
to know the police had the video...

1079
01:11:46.840 --> 01:11:49.200
...that I didn't need
to speak to them myself.

1080
01:11:51.800 --> 01:11:55.400
I thought...
that Carl would be locked up.

1081
01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:44.319
Is Rachel here?
No. No. she's just texted.

1082
01:12:44.320 --> 01:12:47.440
She's gone for a drive with Noah.
Why?

1083
01:12:49.520 --> 01:12:50.760
Noah's got Rachel.

1084
01:12:52.080 --> 01:12:54.840
It really is beautiful.
I told you.

1085
01:12:56.080 --> 01:12:57.920
The trees release
some sort of chemical.

1086
01:12:59.960 --> 01:13:03.760
I can't remember the name of it.
but Maddie told me about it.

1087
01:13:05.920 --> 01:13:07.720
Maddie was amazing.

1088
01:13:09.320 --> 01:13:12.760
She was the only one brave enough
to tell the truth.

1089
01:13:14.320 --> 01:13:16.120
What happens now?

1090
01:13:17.400 --> 01:13:20.080
Do we go back
to protecting the predators?

1091
01:13:21.160 --> 01:13:22.600
Screw that!

1092
01:13:24.320 --> 01:13:26.799
I'm posting the video myself.

1093
01:13:26.800 --> 01:13:30.439
If the uni or the police
won't do anything...

1094
01:13:30.440 --> 01:13:32.040
then I will.

1095
01:13:34.640 --> 01:13:36.160
Rachel. stop.

1096
01:13:39.160 --> 01:13:40.759
What are you doing?

1097
01:13:40.760 --> 01:13:42.759
You were never meant to be involved.

1098
01:13:42.760 --> 01:13:44.839
No!

1099
01:13:47.520 --> 01:13:48.599
No!

1100
01:13:56.760 --> 01:13:58.240
No!

1101
01:14:01.320 --> 01:14:04.519
Nick. check ANPR
and track Noah's phone.

1102
01:14:04.520 --> 01:14:09.159
Last ANPR hit was on the A275.

1103
01:14:09.160 --> 01:14:12.399
heading north
towards Old Mill Forest.

1104
01:14:12.400 --> 01:14:14.519
Trying to track the phone.
I'll get the coordinates.

1105
01:14:14.520 --> 01:14:16.799
Send it through to Vee as well.
She's at the campus.

1106
01:14:16.800 --> 01:14:18.639
She's got a head start on us.

1107
01:14:46.280 --> 01:14:47.360
Noah.

1108
01:14:48.760 --> 01:14:50.160
Please.

1109
01:14:51.840 --> 01:14:53.280
Take me home.

1110
01:14:55.080 --> 01:14:56.400
I can't do that.

1111
01:15:00.280 --> 01:15:02.640
Thing is. Rach.
everyone knows you're depressed.

1112
01:15:04.960 --> 01:15:06.320
So when they find you here...

1113
01:15:08.080 --> 01:15:09.280
...it'll make sense.

1114
01:15:14.240 --> 01:15:15.360
I'm sorry.

1115
01:15:30.040 --> 01:15:32.120
Noah? Noah?

1116
01:16:42.040 --> 01:16:44.840
Rachel? Rachel? Rachel. wake...

1117
01:16:47.960 --> 01:16:49.919
Come on. Rachel! Come on!

1118
01:17:11.920 --> 01:17:14.880
Roy... Vee's car.

1119
01:17:27.320 --> 01:17:28.680
Noah!

1120
01:17:39.960 --> 01:17:43.559
Vee! Vee!

1121
01:17:45.560 --> 01:17:46.760
Come on.

1122
01:17:58.720 --> 01:18:00.080
With me!

1123
01:18:01.880 --> 01:18:03.080
Get her out!

1124
01:18:21.200 --> 01:18:22.920
Gently. Gently.

1125
01:18:24.080 --> 01:18:25.240
That's it.

1126
01:18:26.680 --> 01:18:29.959
Rachel. Rachel. Rachel.

1127
01:18:33.800 --> 01:18:34.959
OK. It's all right.

1128
01:18:39.880 --> 01:18:42.519
Noah Welling.
I'm arresting you for the murders

1129
01:18:42.520 --> 01:18:44.279
of Charlie Downing
and Madeleine Coleman.

1130
01:18:44.280 --> 01:18:45.999
It's Tom Carlton
you should be arresting!

1131
01:18:46.000 --> 01:18:47.399
It may harm your defence...

1132
01:18:47.400 --> 01:18:49.479
He killed my brother.
and you guys did nothing.

1133
01:18:49.480 --> 01:18:50.799
...you later rely on in court...

1134
01:18:50.800 --> 01:18:52.679
That bitch Charlie covered for him.

1135
01:18:52.680 --> 01:18:55.319
...may be given in evidence.
Do you understand?

1136
01:19:09.440 --> 01:19:12.119
When Davey was implicated
in Charlie's murder.

1137
01:19:12.120 --> 01:19:14.359
why didn't you tell us
about your connection?

1138
01:19:14.360 --> 01:19:17.319
With everything going on at the uni.
I...

1139
01:19:17.320 --> 01:19:19.959
I honestly didn't know
if it was linked.

1140
01:19:19.960 --> 01:19:25.920
My testimony caused those boys
so much pain and anger.

1141
01:19:27.840 --> 01:19:31.839
I had so many
unanswered questions...

1142
01:19:31.840 --> 01:19:33.400
about my son's death...

1143
01:19:34.960 --> 01:19:39.240
...one being
whether Charlie's alibi was true.

1144
01:19:40.920 --> 01:19:45.200
In the end. I-I had to accept
what the police told me.

1145
01:19:46.680 --> 01:19:48.200
Or at least try to.

1146
01:19:50.080 --> 01:19:53.760
Well. sadly... Noah didn't.

1147
01:19:56.840 --> 01:19:58.920
I had no idea what he was thinking.

1148
01:20:00.320 --> 01:20:01.520
Planning.

1149
01:20:03.600 --> 01:20:07.159
After Alex died. I pushed them away.
Noah and his mum.

1150
01:20:07.160 --> 01:20:09.760
I didn't want to... but...

1151
01:20:11.640 --> 01:20:12.720
...I was just...

1152
01:20:14.320 --> 01:20:15.680
...so full of pain.

1153
01:20:16.720 --> 01:20:20.320
I had no space for theirs on top.

1154
01:20:23.600 --> 01:20:25.760
My wife left
a year after Alex died.

1155
01:20:29.640 --> 01:20:30.960
I'm so sorry.

1156
01:20:35.400 --> 01:20:37.000
Those poor girls.

1157
01:20:47.600 --> 01:20:48.720
Pause it.

1158
01:20:50.040 --> 01:20:51.240
Zoom in.

1159
01:21:06.920 --> 01:21:10.599
You made a decision
to make Tom and Davey suffer.

1160
01:21:10.600 --> 01:21:11.680
like you suffered.

1161
01:21:13.240 --> 01:21:15.120
Tom Carlton murdered my brother.

1162
01:21:16.480 --> 01:21:18.440
And the police did nothing.

1163
01:21:20.000 --> 01:21:21.040
Why Maddie?

1164
01:21:22.120 --> 01:21:24.239
She saw Charlie in the video.

1165
01:21:24.240 --> 01:21:25.920
She was gonna tell the police.

1166
01:21:28.040 --> 01:21:31.320
Inflicting your own justice
is cathartic. isn't it. Noah?

1167
01:21:33.720 --> 01:21:35.520
Until you get it wrong.

1168
01:21:37.320 --> 01:21:38.800
I didn't get it wrong.

1169
01:21:40.920 --> 01:21:43.440
There was tons of evidence.
You just chose to ignore it.

1170
01:21:51.960 --> 01:21:53.480
I've seen this video before.

1171
01:21:54.840 --> 01:21:58.239
That's Tom murdering my brother.
A witness identified him!

1172
01:21:58.240 --> 01:21:59.999
They identified a man
in a blue hoodie.

1173
01:22:00.000 --> 01:22:01.679
Which was found in Tom's flat.

1174
01:22:01.680 --> 01:22:04.160
That witness was mistaken. Noah.

1175
01:22:08.840 --> 01:22:10.799
Look.

1176
01:22:10.800 --> 01:22:12.080
Look!

1177
01:22:14.440 --> 01:22:16.119
You see the streetlamp?

1178
01:22:16.120 --> 01:22:19.880
The vibrations from the traffic
have made the phosphor fall away.

1179
01:22:21.120 --> 01:22:25.559
So the lamp and everything below it
appears blue.

1180
01:22:25.560 --> 01:22:29.199
The witness thought they saw
the attacker wearing a blue hoodie

1181
01:22:29.200 --> 01:22:30.640
because of the light.

1182
01:22:32.360 --> 01:22:33.760
It was actually grey.

1183
01:22:35.680 --> 01:22:37.320
So he was wearing
a different hoodie.

1184
01:22:38.720 --> 01:22:40.480
That doesn't mean Tom didn't do it.

1185
01:22:43.360 --> 01:22:45.399
He has an alibi in Charlie.

1186
01:22:45.400 --> 01:22:47.080
That alibi was bullshit.

1187
01:22:48.200 --> 01:22:50.680
Charlie lied to save him
just as they were gonna charge him.

1188
01:22:56.160 --> 01:22:58.600
Look at the date and time stamp.

1189
01:23:01.240 --> 01:23:04.199
Tom was nowhere near the bar
that night.

1190
01:23:04.200 --> 01:23:05.680
He was in London with Charlie.

1191
01:23:17.040 --> 01:23:18.280
No.

1192
01:23:20.920 --> 01:23:22.200
No.

1193
01:23:24.200 --> 01:23:26.080
Tom Carlton
did not kill your brother.

1194
01:23:27.480 --> 01:23:31.640
I understand your pain. your anger.
but it was misplaced. Noah.

1195
01:23:32.800 --> 01:23:35.799
An eye for an eye
doesn't bring peace.

1196
01:23:35.800 --> 01:23:39.760
It just creates a cycle of violence
that can be impossible to break.

1197
01:23:42.400 --> 01:23:44.160
But it ends.

1198
01:23:45.360 --> 01:23:46.600
Right here.

1199
01:24:01.400 --> 01:24:02.760
What are you doing here?

1200
01:24:04.720 --> 01:24:06.120
I'm here to see my brother.

1201
01:24:08.480 --> 01:24:09.920
How did it go?

1202
01:24:12.000 --> 01:24:14.200
The recall
to prison's been overturned.

1203
01:24:16.240 --> 01:24:17.840
Man. that's great.

1204
01:24:26.480 --> 01:24:28.400
Well done for today.

1205
01:24:30.160 --> 01:24:33.680
Are you OK?
Yeah. fine. Thanks. though.

1206
01:24:37.640 --> 01:24:41.120
Are you gonna tell me
who the hell this Dennis Tibson is?

1207
01:24:43.960 --> 01:24:48.159
My dad left a message.
told me to go talk to him.

1208
01:24:48.160 --> 01:24:49.320
He reckons...

1209
01:24:50.400 --> 01:24:52.560
...that Cripps is dangerous...

1210
01:24:53.840 --> 01:24:57.760
...and that he framed my dad
for the murder of that informant.

1211
01:24:59.440 --> 01:25:02.920
Maybe my dad had no choice...
when he walked out on me.

1212
01:25:06.360 --> 01:25:08.800
Well. the only way
you're gonna know the truth...

1213
01:25:10.680 --> 01:25:12.080
...is if you talk to him.

1214
01:25:33.360 --> 01:25:36.200
Without you.
we would never have caught Noah.

1215
01:25:37.480 --> 01:25:39.319
And Carl would
still be teaching here.

1216
01:25:39.320 --> 01:25:41.839
He's facing criminal charges.

1217
01:25:41.840 --> 01:25:44.159
and that's all because of you
and Maddie.

1218
01:25:44.160 --> 01:25:45.840
Your bravery.

1219
01:25:48.280 --> 01:25:50.160
She was a trailblazer.

1220
01:25:53.080 --> 01:25:54.600
And I'll keep on the fight.

1221
01:25:56.080 --> 01:26:00.040
Believe me...
we will only get stronger.

1222
01:26:29.800 --> 01:26:32.559
I'm afraid you have to be
a little more specific.

1223
01:26:32.560 --> 01:26:34.800
I have a lot of people call on me.

1224
01:26:42.560 --> 01:26:44.919
Looking for information
on that Nissan.

1225
01:26:44.920 --> 01:26:48.240
It was involved in an accident
on Levisstrasse.

1226
01:26:49.520 --> 01:26:51.320
April 21st.

1227
01:26:52.920 --> 01:26:54.520
You recognise it. don't you?

1228
01:26:57.840 --> 01:27:00.120
Do you know the driver?

1229
01:27:02.200 --> 01:27:05.480
I know him. I sold him that car.

1230
01:27:16.400 --> 01:27:20.040
Does the name Arta Droege
mean anything to you?

1231
01:27:28.960 --> 01:27:30.559
Name the blood vessel

1232
01:27:30.560 --> 01:27:33.439
which carries blood
into the right atrium of the heart.

1233
01:27:36.160 --> 01:27:37.720
Oh. Dad's back.

1234
01:27:40.640 --> 01:27:43.160
I'll... I'll do them upstairs.
Are you sure?

1235
01:27:47.080 --> 01:27:49.240
Hey. Bruno.

1236
01:27:53.360 --> 01:27:54.840
Are you OK?

1237
01:28:02.960 --> 01:28:05.840
Hey.

1238
01:28:07.160 --> 01:28:08.360
Are you OK?

1239
01:28:10.240 --> 01:28:11.520
Not really.

1240
01:28:13.160 --> 01:28:14.560
Come here.

1241
01:28:23.160 --> 01:28:25.680
Sorry.

1242
01:28:27.800 --> 01:28:30.359
I... I have to take this.

1243
01:28:30.360 --> 01:28:31.880
Stay there.

1244
01:28:35.360 --> 01:28:38.919
Glenn?
'Roy. I've got a name.

1245
01:28:38.920 --> 01:28:40.279
'Now I've ran a quick check.

1246
01:28:40.280 --> 01:28:42.879
'and this guy has got a string
of convictions across Europe.

1247
01:28:42.880 --> 01:28:45.239
'I'll pass it onto Marcel.
but if this pays off...'

1248
01:28:45.240 --> 01:28:46.400
It means...

1249
01:28:47.480 --> 01:28:48.960
...Cassian was telling the truth.

1250
01:28:51.200 --> 01:28:53.840
Sandy could have been murdered.
'Yeah.

1251
01:28:55.360 --> 01:28:58.000
'I'm so sorry. Roy.
Let's talk when I get back.'

1252
01:29:03.240 --> 01:29:06.600
I did what you asked.
but they are getting close.

1253
01:29:08.520 --> 01:29:11.120
The cop's name... Glenn Branson.

1254
01:29:12.880 --> 01:29:14.840
He has a wife and two kids.
